1
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:17,480
The legendary search
for the next top models and actors

2
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:21,440
that reshaped the Thai entertainment
and fashion industries is back.

3
00:00:21,520 --> 00:00:25,680
Join me, Kim Goodburn,
on this historic new journey.

4
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:28,600
This is<i> The Face Men Thailand Season 4.</i>

5
00:00:32,759 --> 00:00:36,960
<i>Last week, Mentor Pancake</i>
<i>and Mentor Ananda's Team Panda…</i>

6
00:00:37,040 --> 00:00:38,840
<i>secured their first win.</i>

7
00:00:38,920 --> 00:00:42,200
<i>Thanks to Kimhan's work</i>
<i>in the underwater fashion video campaign.</i>

8
00:00:42,280 --> 00:00:44,040
Beautiful.

9
00:00:44,120 --> 00:00:45,400
Kimhan.

10
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:50,560
<i>Mentor Off had to send a team member</i>
<i>to the Black Room for the first time.</i>

11
00:00:50,640 --> 00:00:53,480
<i>Later, Mentor Ananda decided</i>

12
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:56,080
<i>to eliminate Fox from Team Off.</i>

13
00:00:56,160 --> 00:00:58,680
Fox. You are not The Face.

14
00:00:58,760 --> 00:00:59,840
Thank you.

15
00:00:59,920 --> 00:01:02,600
<i>Now, Team Off and Team Pancake-Ananda</i>

16
00:01:02,680 --> 00:01:04,840
<i>both have only four members left.</i>

17
00:01:04,920 --> 00:01:08,720
<i>Team Mile hasn't won a single campaign,</i>
<i>yet its team remains intact.</i>

18
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:12,080
Why do I feel like the winner? Did we win?

19
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,360
We won, right?

20
00:01:13,440 --> 00:01:16,560
I haven't done much,
but my team is still fully intact.

21
00:01:16,640 --> 00:01:17,600
What should I do?

22
00:01:47,760 --> 00:01:50,280
<i>The winner</i>
<i>of </i>The Face Men Thailand Season 4

23
00:01:50,360 --> 00:01:52,200
<i>will collaborate with Clear Thailand.</i>

24
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:57,440
<i>He will receive a one-year supply</i>
<i>of Clear Ice Cool Menthol.</i>

25
00:01:57,520 --> 00:02:00,000
<i>And get the chance to work</i>
<i>with Vaseline Thailand.</i>

26
00:02:00,080 --> 00:02:03,640
<i>Plus, he'll receive</i>
<i>Vaseline SPF50+ PA++++,</i>

27
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:06,960
<i>Gluta Hyaluronic Acid,</i>
<i>Photoage Defense UV Serum</i>

28
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:08,840
<i>free for an entire year.</i>

29
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:11,120
<i>He will also collaborate with AXE.</i>

30
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:14,320
<i>And receive a year's supply</i>
<i>of personal care products.</i>

31
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:17,800
<i>Bearbeary, only the wearers feel it.</i>

32
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:21,680
<i>Premium wear for every style,</i>
<i>featuring top design and innovation.</i>

33
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:23,920
<i>They'll award a 100,000-baht gift voucher.</i>

34
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:28,080
<i>Strive for perfection</i>
<i>with a membership to Hotman Fitness.</i>

35
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:31,480
<i>Including an 18-month</i>
<i>personal training program.</i>

36
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:34,880
<i>Plus a 200,000-baht package</i>
<i>from V Design Clinic.</i>

37
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:36,960
<i>Get ready to step onto the national screen</i>

38
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:40,520
<i>through a collaboration</i>
<i>with Channel 3 HD, Thailand.</i>

39
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:44,600
<i>And sign an acting contract</i>
<i>with Kantana Group Public Company Limited,</i>

40
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:47,200
<i>Thailand's leading producer</i>
<i>of dramas and films.</i>

41
00:03:27,720 --> 00:03:30,200
- Nice new leather shoes.
- And?

42
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:32,560
- I want them.
- Send me a screenshot.

43
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:33,640
- Snap this?
- Yes.

44
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:36,480
Did you get it?

45
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:39,200
- Look. Did I get it right?
- Exactly.

46
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:42,160
Check them out on Shopee.
Snap, search, and buy.

47
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:43,520
Exactly. That's so easy.

48
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:45,320
Great deals with fast delivery.

49
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:47,120
It truly has it all.

50
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:56,760
- Hello, everyone.
- Hello.

51
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:58,080
This is Episode 4.

52
00:03:58,160 --> 00:03:59,280
The halfway mark.

53
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:00,920
I'm ready for whatever comes.

54
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:03,720
All right, let's dive right
into today's master class.

55
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:08,400
Today, we're covering a crucial foundation
of the fashion industry.

56
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:12,160
You will all learn how to create
your signature pose.

57
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:15,040
A pose that will make you memorable
in every single frame.

58
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:17,519
So, please give a big
round of applause for…

59
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:19,160
Mentor Ananda and Mentor Off!

60
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:23,840
I haven't learned from Mentor Ananda yet.

61
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,720
As soon as he walked in…

62
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:29,160
I knew a whole new world
was about to open up.

63
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:31,040
Let's get straight to the point.

64
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:33,080
- Let's start with Mentor Ananda.
- Sure.

65
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:38,120
How important is a signature pose
in the fashion industry?

66
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:41,240
Having a signature pose
is all about highlighting

67
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:42,560
your uniqueness.

68
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:44,760
Your true identity and character.

69
00:04:44,840 --> 00:04:47,120
It's what makes you stand out.

70
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:50,640
When people see your photos,
your poses, your vibe,

71
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:52,120
they should recognize you.

72
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:55,840
So, uniqueness and posing
are both crucial.

73
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:59,440
But what I'm really looking for today
is confidence.

74
00:04:59,520 --> 00:05:03,240
Anyone can strike a cool pose.
Anyone can do that.

75
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:05,200
But that doesn't show who you are.

76
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:07,400
How do you want people to see you?

77
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:09,800
Confident, collected, or charismatic?

78
00:05:09,880 --> 00:05:12,680
It all depends on your interpretation.

79
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:16,440
Having your own signature pose
makes you memorable.

80
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:19,520
I'm sure I can find my own signature.

81
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:21,200
Even if we strike the same pose,

82
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:23,520
my personal touch makes it uniquely mine.

83
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,880
I bring my own energy to it.

84
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:28,520
For today's challenge,
we'll focus on movement.

85
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:32,200
Move freely and find your perfect pose.

86
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:37,080
It's simple. We'll play some music.
I want you to feel the beat and dance.

87
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:40,120
We'll stop the music
and you'll have to freeze.

88
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:42,680
Freeze.

89
00:05:42,760 --> 00:05:44,160
Okay, that's your pose.

90
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:47,880
I only know one dance move,
but once the music plays, I'll feel it.

91
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:49,920
Can I pull off my own signature pose?

92
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,280
I hope so.

93
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:52,640
I hope it's a good one.

94
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:54,720
Not just a funny one.

95
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:57,480
Okay, let's have
the first six contestants.

96
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:59,440
- Start with Kimhan to Bonus,
- Bonus.

97
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:00,600
you are the first six.

98
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:02,120
Hit the music.

99
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:06,760
When the music hit,
my body might be stiff,

100
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:08,760
but my hips knew the beat.

101
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:12,280
My hips went first, and the rest followed.
My hips were very ready.

102
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:17,840
You'll get in trouble
before you discover your signature pose.

103
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:24,080
The vibe was pumping. I felt confident.

104
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:26,400
I was like, "Bring it on! Take this!"

105
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:28,960
Like I totally owned the place.

106
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:30,520
Look at him, he's out of control.

107
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,520
I couldn't wait.

108
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:35,360
My happy feet wanted to dance.

109
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:38,240
- Okay, that's it.
- That's it.

110
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:39,920
- Look.
- Keep on moving.

111
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,320
Look.

112
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:45,320
Leo is a handsome guy,
but he dances as stiff as a tree.

113
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:48,160
Have you seen a scarecrow
swaying in the wind?

114
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:51,560
- Look.
- He's getting it.

115
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:52,840
- That's it!
- That's it!

116
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:54,320
- Fierce move!
- That's it!

117
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:56,640
I just went with the flow.

118
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:59,040
Full Thai country boy style.
I just went for it.

119
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,480
I was all over the place.

120
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:02,680
Full-on Thai street dancing
with a tour-bus style.

121
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:03,800
Nice.

122
00:07:03,880 --> 00:07:06,520
- Hey!
- Nice.

123
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,320
More, more!

124
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,920
- I want to dance with them.
- Go!

125
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:12,480
Good, I think it's relaxing.

126
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:14,760
Today's class is pretty chill.

127
00:07:14,840 --> 00:07:15,800
Nice, they're cute.

128
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:19,040
We get to see their personalities.
A lot of them can't really dance.

129
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:22,880
Just like me.

130
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:30,280
The first group just let loose.
They expressed themselves well.

131
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:31,400
It was good.

132
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:32,960
They worked together well.

133
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:35,520
I would consider it a pass.

134
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,960
- But the legs.
- He's fine.

135
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:39,720
The legs might need
to look more masculine.

136
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:43,480
Okay, what about the face?
I saw you biting your lip a bit.

137
00:07:44,160 --> 00:07:46,400
Oh, sticking your tongue out? You'll see.

138
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:48,680
Let me smack that.

139
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:51,800
Pom and I were like
separated lovers at that moment.

140
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:54,480
Ever since I won, he's been mad at me.
I can feel it.

141
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:59,440
The lean is good,
but maybe bring this hand up a bit.

142
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:01,080
And lean down.

143
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,840
Your legs are too parallel.

144
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:04,560
Try stretching your left leg out.

145
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:06,760
- Right.
- Yes, okay. Much better.

146
00:08:06,840 --> 00:08:08,400
They were too even just now.

147
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:10,560
A tiny tweak made it look cool.

148
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:13,440
Easy. I don't need to do anything
or change him at all.

149
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:14,560
He looks natural.

150
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:18,760
I was happy seeing everyone relax
and go with the flow.

151
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:20,240
Some had awkward poses.

152
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:24,880
It was good. Everyone got to relax,
and most did well.

153
00:08:24,960 --> 00:08:26,800
You stopped with this pose.

154
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:28,080
Yes, like this.

155
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:29,000
- Well…
- Oh, wow.

156
00:08:29,080 --> 00:08:31,000
If you make a horny face, it's over.

157
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:32,360
No, just a straight face.

158
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:36,520
His pose was very provocative.
His hand was almost on his crotch.

159
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:38,240
The other hand behind.

160
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:40,000
That was just my dance move.

161
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:42,600
It won't work with just a pose,
so I just went with it.

162
00:08:42,679 --> 00:08:44,920
It was up to him if he could change me.

163
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,240
I challenged him.

164
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:48,440
Just now, you froze up, right?

165
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:50,320
Sometimes it has to be like…

166
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:52,360
Find a starting point, then pose.

167
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:54,000
Yes, something like that.

168
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:56,880
Bonus is naturally cheeky.

169
00:08:56,960 --> 00:09:00,560
So his signature pose
needs some of that cheekiness

170
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:02,560
to match his personality.

171
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:04,480
Next six contestants, please.

172
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:12,280
I pictured it in my head
and followed that.

173
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:15,040
I think confidence is crucial because…

174
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:18,360
You can express whatever feeling you want.

175
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:20,400
You can just wing it.

176
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:22,320
You can spin or do whatever you want.

177
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:23,600
That's it.

178
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:26,680
Pom is going all out.

179
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:28,600
Wow, it was fun. Seriously.

180
00:09:28,680 --> 00:09:31,200
I danced as if no one else was there.

181
00:09:31,280 --> 00:09:32,200
Just move it.

182
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:37,400
Dancing it out relieves anxiety.
That is the feeling it needs.

183
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:41,040
Have fun. Do whatever you want.

184
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:46,720
- Okay.
- Look. Jacob's pose doesn't look strong.

185
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:48,520
- It looks like…
- Tug-of-war.

186
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:50,760
Your face doesn't need to be like that.

187
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:54,480
Maybe just squint a bit,
because just now, you did this.

188
00:09:55,160 --> 00:09:57,040
"So tired." You're not actually tired.

189
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:59,200
It's just a tired look, like this.

190
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:00,440
Better.

191
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:02,600
It didn't look strong at first.

192
00:10:02,680 --> 00:10:05,880
Then Ananda adjusted my expression
to show more inner emotion.

193
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:07,680
I have to convey the emotion.

194
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:09,880
That's it, PP. Lift this leg up.

195
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:12,000
- Good.
- Good.

196
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:13,560
Once you have the pose,

197
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:15,360
- next is the face.
- The face.

198
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:16,440
Okay, Pom, first.

199
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:20,120
Pom had so much fun dancing
and changing poses.

200
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,560
But he ended up with this.

201
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:26,320
You did all those dance moves
just to end up in this pose?

202
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:28,160
Try looking up a bit.

203
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:30,640
- Hand up.
- Like you're blocking the light.

204
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:32,200
Okay, something like this.

205
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:34,360
The second group seemed better overall.

206
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:36,400
They seemed more relaxed and natural.

207
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:39,920
They listened, learned,
and showed more curiosity.

208
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:44,800
You've all learned
how to find your signature poses.

209
00:10:44,880 --> 00:10:49,600
Now, it's time to take
what you've just learned

210
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:52,200
and put it to the test.

211
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:55,400
Let's get our master class challenge.

212
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:58,240
Please welcome the person
presenting today's challenge,

213
00:10:58,320 --> 00:11:00,440
legendary photographer,

214
00:11:00,520 --> 00:11:02,400
Wasan Puengprasert, known as Ple.

215
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:05,760
Hello.

216
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:08,920
WASAN PUENGPRASERT
THAILAND'S LEADING FASHION PHOTOGRAPHER

217
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:11,760
We also have another guest today

218
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:14,080
joining us for this challenge.

219
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:16,320
A leading Thai designer

220
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:19,120
and a former mentor on <i>The Face</i>,

221
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:21,560
Moo, Asava founder, Polpat Asavaprapha.

222
00:11:26,040 --> 00:11:29,280
POLPAT ASAVAPRAPHA
FORMER THE FACE MENTOR, ASAVA FOUNDER

223
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:32,440
Let's talk about
today's master class challenge.

224
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:33,840
What's the challenge, Ple?

225
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:38,040
Your challenge is "The Iconic God."

226
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:40,920
Become a living sculpture
for a photoshoot.

227
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:45,400
Channel your essence
to express who you are

228
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:47,200
while keeping it iconic,

229
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:49,520
distinct, and unique.

230
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:51,880
That's the key to this challenge.

231
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:56,760
My signature pose
will be all about contrast.

232
00:11:56,840 --> 00:11:59,480
Cool but provocative.

233
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:00,920
Reflecting myself a bit.

234
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,560
I only need one shot.

235
00:12:02,640 --> 00:12:06,360
I'll pose like this
with the light shining down.

236
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:07,600
Something like that.

237
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:12,360
Being iconic means making
the audience feel the emotion

238
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:16,600
and story each god is trying to tell.

239
00:12:16,680 --> 00:12:19,920
It requires both emotion
and the right pose

240
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:23,320
to make your body look captivating

241
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:26,440
and to use your body to your advantage.

242
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:28,040
That's the job of every model.

243
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:29,280
It won't be easy.

244
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:32,000
Oh, the god is here.

245
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:34,800
This is my time to shine. I'm so ready.

246
00:12:34,880 --> 00:12:37,800
Let's see if I can impress
the judges today.

247
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:41,560
Here are the rules
for today's master class.

248
00:12:41,640 --> 00:12:45,400
Today, everyone will do a photoshoot

249
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:48,520
under the concept of "The Iconic God."

250
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:52,920
You'll be body-painted
and posing on a pedestal.

251
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:56,960
Only one minute for the shoot.

252
00:12:57,040 --> 00:12:59,520
Twenty seconds is enough. Even five.

253
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:00,720
One pose. Bam!

254
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:03,400
I won't play it safe today.
I'm going to be a god.

255
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:09,160
What are the judging criteria, Ple?

256
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:12,320
The two of us will review
and select the photos.

257
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:15,880
Then, discuss who the winner is.

258
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:18,240
All right, now you know the challenge

259
00:13:18,320 --> 00:13:20,760
and the judging criteria.

260
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:22,840
- Are you ready?
- Ready!

261
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:24,160
If you're ready,

262
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:27,240
prepare yourself
for "The Iconic God" challenge.

263
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:30,960
My only competition

264
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:32,960
is myself.

265
00:13:33,040 --> 00:13:36,040
I'm winning this for Fox.

266
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:40,000
I'm so ready. More than ready, seriously.

267
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:44,440
This round, I'll put Team Panda
in the top three.

268
00:13:52,520 --> 00:13:54,480
Welcome back to today's master class

269
00:13:54,560 --> 00:13:57,600
with "The Iconic God"
fashion photoshoot challenge.

270
00:13:57,680 --> 00:14:00,000
But before bringing out the contestants,

271
00:14:00,080 --> 00:14:04,560
you heard the track, "Bosh,"
earlier from our alumna.

272
00:14:04,640 --> 00:14:06,600
We're honored to have her today

273
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:09,200
as a guest judge for this master class.

274
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:12,120
Please give a big hand for MellaMay

275
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:13,960
from <i>The Face Thailand Season 6</i>.

276
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,400
She's an alumna here.

277
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:21,160
She must understand how things work here.

278
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:25,520
Let's see who MellaMay and Moo

279
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:28,240
will choose as the winner.

280
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:31,520
I believe our contestants are ready.

281
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:34,160
So, let's welcome our first one, Lincoln.

282
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:47,160
When Lincoln came out,

283
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:50,080
he looked like a god and was covered
head to toe in white paint.

284
00:14:50,160 --> 00:14:51,440
Except for his red eyes.

285
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:53,640
He looked like a demon on camera.

286
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:55,320
So much power.

287
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:56,400
So powerful.

288
00:15:03,760 --> 00:15:04,840
Let's see how it goes.

289
00:15:04,920 --> 00:15:08,360
- I like how he went a bit dark.
- It's more like…

290
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:11,040
the opposite of a traditional statue.
Very demonic.

291
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:17,120
Lincoln did great.
He had great ideas and creativity.

292
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:20,080
But he lacked variety.

293
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:22,200
Next up, please welcome Leo.

294
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:24,480
Oh, wow. Hello.

295
00:15:24,560 --> 00:15:26,840
- This is scary.
- His body is great.

296
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:30,080
Leo's physique looks like
that of a Greek god.

297
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:32,040
Already looks like a statue.

298
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:33,520
Okay.

299
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,520
- He has worry in his eyes.
- His eyes…

300
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:40,200
- Yes.
- The last guy had fierce eyes.

301
00:15:40,280 --> 00:15:42,320
But this one clearly looks worried.

302
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:46,360
Leo isn't expressing much emotion.

303
00:15:46,440 --> 00:15:50,080
The emotion he conveyed at first
was pure anxiety.

304
00:15:50,160 --> 00:15:53,480
It feels like too many thoughts
are weighing on him.

305
00:15:53,560 --> 00:15:55,280
Shame. He has a great physique.

306
00:15:57,920 --> 00:16:00,320
His first pose was the best.

307
00:16:03,560 --> 00:16:05,040
The fluke shot is the best.

308
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:06,800
This one is good.

309
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:10,520
It was in the last two seconds…

310
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:11,800
He posed like this.

311
00:16:11,880 --> 00:16:15,000
He fell, but it was a magical moment.

312
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:18,640
Everything was spot on. I was stunned.

313
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:21,640
Yes, I guess that was a magical moment.

314
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:23,960
Let's move on
to our third contestant, Rome.

315
00:16:24,560 --> 00:16:26,760
- Start the clock.
- Okay, Rome, come on.

316
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:29,680
I focus on the word "god."

317
00:16:29,760 --> 00:16:32,000
I'm a god. That was my interpretation.

318
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:35,880
I tried to create grand,
over-the-top poses.

319
00:16:35,960 --> 00:16:39,120
Now, try standing up straight.

320
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:40,400
Don't overwork it.

321
00:16:40,480 --> 00:16:42,200
You need to understand your character.

322
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:44,520
Keep it straight and simple. Okay.

323
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:47,760
For a moment, I tried to stay still.

324
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:50,080
Then I was overthinking it.

325
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:54,080
I thought the photo
had to look extremely grand.

326
00:16:54,160 --> 00:16:57,320
He's stuck in his old modeling habits.

327
00:16:57,400 --> 00:17:01,040
Cool expressions and poses.
Those are wrong here.

328
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:03,520
It's not bad, though.

329
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:05,280
But it doesn't fit the brief.

330
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:06,560
Time's up!

331
00:17:09,760 --> 00:17:11,280
- Not quite there yet.
- Yes.

332
00:17:11,359 --> 00:17:15,000
Not good. No one clapped.

333
00:17:15,079 --> 00:17:15,920
Except Kim.

334
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:17,760
And he only did it to be polite.

335
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:19,319
I crumbled.

336
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:23,520
He did well, but I actually expected more.

337
00:17:23,599 --> 00:17:25,560
Next up, Peem.

338
00:17:25,640 --> 00:17:27,240
- Oh, wow.
- Oh, wow.

339
00:17:27,319 --> 00:17:28,520
Dark vibes.

340
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:31,680
For those who just tuned in,
I'm not a ghost.

341
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:34,080
I just fell into a bucket of paint.

342
00:17:35,040 --> 00:17:37,120
If you're ready, start the clock.

343
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:40,080
- Good.
- This might be it.

344
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:43,320
Move slightly. Slowly.

345
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:45,240
- Yes.
- Yes, move a little.

346
00:17:45,320 --> 00:17:46,840
Stand straight and hand down.

347
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:50,360
- Try the other pedestal.
- Move, move.

348
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:53,520
- He only has one pose.
- For the overall.

349
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:55,360
There's no variety.

350
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:57,800
One minute is enough to try various poses.

351
00:17:57,880 --> 00:18:01,400
Not sure why he kept doing the same pose.

352
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:06,400
It's a shame.
He's more creative than that.

353
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:07,560
Only one minute…

354
00:18:07,640 --> 00:18:10,000
I always feel time is running out.

355
00:18:10,080 --> 00:18:11,600
Like no time to think.

356
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:15,640
What a pity. I expected more.

357
00:18:17,760 --> 00:18:18,760
Next is Mew.

358
00:18:18,840 --> 00:18:20,240
Come on.

359
00:18:21,120 --> 00:18:23,120
I saw the set and got excited.

360
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:26,160
I knew I could do it. It's all in my head.

361
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:31,240
- Pose! Good.
- I like that sensual vibe. Nice.

362
00:18:31,320 --> 00:18:32,280
Very good.

363
00:18:32,360 --> 00:18:35,720
Before the shoot,
I had already pictured my poses.

364
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:38,920
I found my rhythm with the photographer.

365
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:40,560
Many good shots today.

366
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:41,800
Forty seconds left.

367
00:18:41,880 --> 00:18:43,000
- Nice.
- Very good.

368
00:18:43,080 --> 00:18:45,720
- More emotion on your face.
- Like that.

369
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:47,560
Beautiful.

370
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:50,280
- Last 30 seconds.
- Gorgeous.

371
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:53,640
- I love the emotion.
- And the boldness.

372
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:54,560
The best.

373
00:18:54,640 --> 00:18:58,400
Mew really surprised me
in this master class.

374
00:18:58,480 --> 00:18:59,600
He gave his all.

375
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:04,040
- Last ten seconds. Nine, eight, seven.
- Very good.

376
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:05,640
- Six, five.
- Hands up.

377
00:19:06,240 --> 00:19:10,760
- Four, three, two, one. Time's up.
- Oh, wow.

378
00:19:11,480 --> 00:19:13,000
Lots of great shots.

379
00:19:13,080 --> 00:19:17,000
The judges should love him,
just like I do.

380
00:19:17,080 --> 00:19:18,560
He's at the top of his game.

381
00:19:18,640 --> 00:19:20,040
He's definitely the winner.

382
00:19:20,120 --> 00:19:22,160
Can I say that? Is it too cocky?

383
00:19:22,240 --> 00:19:28,080
Team Off did well. He kept smiling
beside me. I'll give it to him this time.

384
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:29,240
He was like…

385
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:31,680
Jacob, you're up.

386
00:19:31,760 --> 00:19:32,720
Okay, let's start.

387
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:35,320
- Easy, easy.
- Easy.

388
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:36,320
He's panicked.

389
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:38,000
- It will be tough.
- Time start.

390
00:19:38,080 --> 00:19:41,720
Jacob didn't do so well.
He wasn't that memorable.

391
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:45,640
His poses were repetitive and stiff.
So he didn't shine.

392
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:49,240
Mew is a tough act to follow.

393
00:19:49,320 --> 00:19:51,960
Next up, Donut. Start the clock.

394
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:54,600
Wow, his eyes.

395
00:19:55,680 --> 00:19:58,080
I don't know where he got that energy.

396
00:19:58,160 --> 00:20:01,440
He came in with a deadpan,
serious expression, and looked tense.

397
00:20:01,520 --> 00:20:03,920
Some kind of tension.

398
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,840
Let's move on to Bonus.

399
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:10,120
Bonus was totally in character.
He stepped up ready.

400
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:12,600
- Start the clock.
- He's stressed.

401
00:20:12,680 --> 00:20:14,880
Yes, he's usually playful. He's like…

402
00:20:14,960 --> 00:20:16,480
He looks stressed.

403
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:19,240
I wasn't stressed. I was in the zone.

404
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:21,600
Bonus was probably thinking hard.

405
00:20:21,680 --> 00:20:24,520
He probably had a clear concept in mind.

406
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:26,120
That he's a Greek god.

407
00:20:28,080 --> 00:20:30,360
- Contact with the camera.
- Twenty seconds.

408
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:31,880
- At the camera.
- Look here.

409
00:20:31,960 --> 00:20:35,000
- Tell a story in your head.
- Fifteen seconds left.

410
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:37,320
- Your message.
- The other pedestal.

411
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:38,720
I heard it, but didn't follow.

412
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:40,000
I won't. I'll be myself.

413
00:20:40,080 --> 00:20:43,360
Listen? Please.
You don't tell a god what to do.

414
00:20:43,440 --> 00:20:46,200
He looked stressed,
and the photos delivered nothing.

415
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:47,480
He showed one emotion.

416
00:20:47,560 --> 00:20:51,440
He misinterpreted it,
trying too hard to play a god.

417
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:52,880
All intense and stiff.

418
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:55,600
If he were on my team,
I would retrain him.

419
00:20:56,120 --> 00:20:58,840
The brief wasn't to be stressed,
but to be strong.

420
00:20:58,920 --> 00:21:01,880
I misunderstood the brief a bit.
I came out totally stiff.

421
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:02,800
Total stone.

422
00:21:04,960 --> 00:21:06,640
Next up, Manyoo.

423
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:07,960
Don't stress too much.

424
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:10,120
Three, two, one, start.

425
00:21:11,960 --> 00:21:14,360
Manyoo doesn't have to pose much.

426
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:17,080
His cool, calm energy is enough.

427
00:21:17,160 --> 00:21:19,560
Nice. Hold still. Okay.

428
00:21:19,640 --> 00:21:21,480
- Better.
- This half shot is nice.

429
00:21:21,560 --> 00:21:23,200
- He looks like a Thai icon.
- Yes.

430
00:21:23,280 --> 00:21:25,480
- A Thai monument.
- The half-body is nice.

431
00:21:25,560 --> 00:21:27,520
You know the Victory Monument statues?

432
00:21:27,600 --> 00:21:29,960
Looks the same. Amazing shots.

433
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:32,280
Like an authentic Thai sculpture.

434
00:21:32,360 --> 00:21:34,240
Next up, Pom.

435
00:21:36,560 --> 00:21:39,920
Pom, you have one minute.
Time starts when you're ready.

436
00:21:40,680 --> 00:21:42,720
- Bring good energy!
- Focus!

437
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:44,800
- Beautiful. That works.
- That's it, man.

438
00:21:44,880 --> 00:21:46,480
No pressure at all.

439
00:21:46,560 --> 00:21:50,720
Before the shoot,
I was practicing poses by myself.

440
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:52,320
Wow, beautiful.

441
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:53,440
I expect a lot.

442
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:56,640
I want him to do well anyway.

443
00:21:56,720 --> 00:21:58,720
Nice. That squatting pose was great.

444
00:21:58,800 --> 00:22:03,400
- Yes, beautiful.
- Oh, wow!

445
00:22:03,480 --> 00:22:06,160
Fabulous. Pom is so talented.

446
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:08,480
He's a threat.
I'm glad we're on the same team.

447
00:22:08,560 --> 00:22:13,400
Pom is a top contender.
He's definitely the one to beat.

448
00:22:13,480 --> 00:22:16,040
It's hard to bend over
and still look tall.

449
00:22:16,120 --> 00:22:18,680
- But he pulled it off.
- Yes, he…

450
00:22:18,760 --> 00:22:20,720
He uses his body very well.

451
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:23,080
Every pose was excellent.

452
00:22:23,160 --> 00:22:24,880
His body lines are incredible.

453
00:22:24,960 --> 00:22:28,120
Pom gave his all, like Mew did.

454
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:34,040
- Five, four, three, two, one. Time's up!
- Wow, lots of great shots.

455
00:22:34,120 --> 00:22:35,200
Many good ones.

456
00:22:35,280 --> 00:22:36,400
Great job.

457
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:38,440
Both Pom and Mew are top contenders.

458
00:22:38,520 --> 00:22:42,320
If they don't win today,
Ple had better have a good explanation.

459
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:47,200
The audience can also see it.
It's really good.

460
00:22:47,840 --> 00:22:48,880
I don't want to brag.

461
00:22:48,960 --> 00:22:50,800
Next up, PP.

462
00:22:50,880 --> 00:22:54,000
- Yes, wow.
- Yes.

463
00:22:54,080 --> 00:22:55,120
This was made for me.

464
00:22:55,200 --> 00:22:58,400
My body and hairstyle are perfect for it.

465
00:22:58,480 --> 00:23:02,280
I think my physique
really fits the "god" theme.

466
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:06,040
- Start!
- Show me this statue.

467
00:23:06,120 --> 00:23:07,280
Interesting.

468
00:23:07,360 --> 00:23:09,440
- Remember to look at the camera.
- Slowly.

469
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:11,760
Beautiful. Slowly.

470
00:23:11,840 --> 00:23:15,240
PP looks just like a Greek god.
Pale skin and curly hair.

471
00:23:15,320 --> 00:23:18,040
He has a huge advantage.

472
00:23:18,120 --> 00:23:19,440
PP had the smoothest run.

473
00:23:19,520 --> 00:23:21,320
Lots of fluid movements.

474
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:23,000
He got many good shots.

475
00:23:23,080 --> 00:23:26,120
It's interesting.
I would say he's a top contender.

476
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:30,200
Now, our final contestant.
Please welcome Kimhan.

477
00:23:31,960 --> 00:23:35,080
I may look confident,
but my mind was actually blank.

478
00:23:35,160 --> 00:23:36,480
I was just improvising.

479
00:23:36,560 --> 00:23:37,920
Time starts now!

480
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:39,800
- That was good.
- Oh, wow.

481
00:23:39,880 --> 00:23:41,320
Quite a unique pose.

482
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:43,320
My family business was in marble.

483
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:47,280
So I'm very familiar with it.

484
00:23:47,360 --> 00:23:48,480
Very much.

485
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:52,160
One good thing about him

486
00:23:52,240 --> 00:23:55,400
is that his relaxed vibe
comes through so well.

487
00:23:55,480 --> 00:23:56,680
It works very well.

488
00:23:56,760 --> 00:23:59,120
Yes, that's it. Very good.

489
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:00,400
Excellent.

490
00:24:00,480 --> 00:24:03,720
I planned to do something
the others wouldn't do.

491
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:05,720
I was the first one to use the fabric.

492
00:24:05,800 --> 00:24:07,360
Why didn't anyone else?

493
00:24:07,440 --> 00:24:11,280
What a waste. It was beautifully painted.

494
00:24:12,280 --> 00:24:16,480
Everything he does is interesting.
It makes me want to keep watching.

495
00:24:16,560 --> 00:24:20,560
The brief said "unique,"
and that's exactly what he did.

496
00:24:20,640 --> 00:24:22,640
Using the fabric was very outside the box.

497
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:26,720
In terms of creativity,
Kimhan stood out the most.

498
00:24:27,320 --> 00:24:33,680
- Five, four, three, two.
- Arch your back more. Yes, like that.

499
00:24:33,760 --> 00:24:35,560
Everyone was stunned.

500
00:24:35,640 --> 00:24:38,960
I have to admit, he was the only one
thinking outside the box.

501
00:24:39,040 --> 00:24:43,400
- Wow, this really looks like marble.
- Exactly like marble.

502
00:24:44,040 --> 00:24:48,120
Kimhan is dangerous.
I'll say less about him. He won last time.

503
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:49,400
I'll keep it brief.

504
00:24:50,120 --> 00:24:52,400
Just now, all 12 contestants

505
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:55,120
showed us their take on "The Iconic God"

506
00:24:55,200 --> 00:24:57,040
in our fashion photoshoot.

507
00:24:57,120 --> 00:24:59,560
Now, let's take a look at the photos.

508
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:05,720
Let's hear what the judges
and mentors have to say.

509
00:25:05,800 --> 00:25:07,560
Let's start with Ple.

510
00:25:07,640 --> 00:25:11,720
I'm quite proud of all the contestants.

511
00:25:12,240 --> 00:25:16,560
I can see how you've reinvented yourselves

512
00:25:16,640 --> 00:25:19,600
through each of your living sculptures.

513
00:25:19,680 --> 00:25:22,640
It made the photos even more beautiful.

514
00:25:22,720 --> 00:25:24,960
Focus and determination are important.

515
00:25:25,040 --> 00:25:27,240
But you also need to stay relaxed.

516
00:25:27,320 --> 00:25:29,400
Follow the photographer's direction

517
00:25:29,480 --> 00:25:34,360
for smoother workflow
and appealing photos.

518
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:38,800
Get in sync with the photographer.

519
00:25:38,880 --> 00:25:42,960
The brief is "strong and iconic,"
not "stressed."

520
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:45,040
So relax and take a breath.

521
00:25:45,840 --> 00:25:48,200
- Don't look stressed.
- Don't be.

522
00:25:48,280 --> 00:25:51,320
I liked their emotions and stories.

523
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:53,560
Every concept was clear. Great job.

524
00:25:53,640 --> 00:25:57,000
Your interpretation
and camera engagement were great.

525
00:25:57,080 --> 00:25:58,920
- Everyone did a great job.
- Yes.

526
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:00,200
You all shone today.

527
00:26:00,280 --> 00:26:02,920
I'm impressed. Good job, you all.

528
00:26:05,840 --> 00:26:10,280
I'm so proud.
I'm confident many of the photos worked.

529
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:13,760
These are the top three photos
from the master class.

530
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:19,120
I said I would do this for Fox.

531
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:22,920
My photo is one of those.
I'm getting closer to my goal.

532
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:24,000
Stay for feedback.

533
00:26:24,080 --> 00:26:25,800
Kimhan made it too?

534
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:28,920
Mew and I from Team Off are there.

535
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:30,160
How did Kimhan make it in?

536
00:26:30,240 --> 00:26:32,880
Pom again? He's getting annoying.

537
00:26:32,960 --> 00:26:34,520
Why is it always the two of us?

538
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:36,600
Maybe it's fate.

539
00:26:38,040 --> 00:26:40,840
All right, let's critique each photo.

540
00:26:40,920 --> 00:26:41,800
Pom is up first.

541
00:26:41,880 --> 00:26:45,640
Pom gave us plenty of choices of photos.

542
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:48,200
None of his shots looks awkward.

543
00:26:48,280 --> 00:26:53,200
Besides, his poses are on point,
which makes every shot look flattering.

544
00:26:53,280 --> 00:26:54,600
And the next photo.

545
00:26:54,680 --> 00:26:58,600
This photo is powerful,
and I really like it.

546
00:26:58,680 --> 00:27:01,800
It goes perfectly with my lighting.

547
00:27:01,880 --> 00:27:03,840
What do you think of the last photo?

548
00:27:03,920 --> 00:27:07,720
This photo tells the best story.

549
00:27:07,800 --> 00:27:08,840
Maybe not the best,

550
00:27:08,920 --> 00:27:11,080
but it tells a story.

551
00:27:11,160 --> 00:27:16,200
Kimhan must have had a lot on his mind,
and he wanted to express it all.

552
00:27:16,280 --> 00:27:18,040
We can feel it just by looking.

553
00:27:18,120 --> 00:27:20,800
This is great. Excellent work.

554
00:27:22,080 --> 00:27:23,320
I know. I know.

555
00:27:23,400 --> 00:27:26,120
Stop it. You're making me blush.

556
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:27,040
Ple.

557
00:27:27,600 --> 00:27:32,840
Who channeled "The Iconic God" best today?

558
00:27:32,920 --> 00:27:34,200
Can I pick two people?

559
00:27:34,280 --> 00:27:35,240
- What?
- Oh, my.

560
00:27:35,320 --> 00:27:36,600
Can I pick two?

561
00:27:36,680 --> 00:27:37,840
- Sure.
- Because…

562
00:27:37,920 --> 00:27:41,560
Both nailed the brief. Their photos convey
completely different moods.

563
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:45,920
So, since I have to decide, I choose…

564
00:27:48,640 --> 00:27:49,600
Pom and Mew.

565
00:27:53,600 --> 00:27:55,680
- I want to hug them, but better not.
- Cute.

566
00:27:56,960 --> 00:27:59,120
I'm so happy. So thrilled.

567
00:27:59,200 --> 00:28:01,400
We nailed both
the light and dark concepts.

568
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:03,960
I'm over the moon somehow.

569
00:28:04,040 --> 00:28:07,800
My team has proven it.
They gave their all to win.

570
00:28:07,880 --> 00:28:13,720
I'm glad to hear that Mew and I made it.
Everyone really did it for Fox.

571
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:16,440
Oh, we actually did it.

572
00:28:16,520 --> 00:28:19,960
We made a real comeback
after losing one of our members.

573
00:28:20,040 --> 00:28:22,640
It's a two-for-one deal!

574
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:25,920
That's just too much.

575
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:29,280
See? Off is going to be so smug
now that he has two winners.

576
00:28:29,360 --> 00:28:30,760
That hurts the most.

577
00:28:31,720 --> 00:28:33,640
For the others watching,

578
00:28:33,720 --> 00:28:36,480
brace yourselves.
The real game starts now.

579
00:28:37,400 --> 00:28:38,960
Sorry, but we're done losing.

580
00:28:39,040 --> 00:28:41,600
And of course,
I would like to thank the judges

581
00:28:41,680 --> 00:28:44,520
for joining our master class today.

582
00:28:44,600 --> 00:28:47,000
- Thank you so much, Ple and Moo.
- Thank you.

583
00:28:47,080 --> 00:28:48,800
- Thank you, MellaMay.
- Thank you.

584
00:28:48,880 --> 00:28:51,840
But our competition isn't over yet.

585
00:28:51,920 --> 00:28:55,520
The real campaign
will bring you more pressure.

586
00:28:55,600 --> 00:28:56,640
Be ready.

587
00:28:56,720 --> 00:28:58,680
Because the real challenge is up next.

588
00:29:03,080 --> 00:29:05,680
A head start.
Last time, his team got one perk.

589
00:29:05,760 --> 00:29:07,360
This time, they got two.

590
00:29:07,440 --> 00:29:09,200
Just you wait in the campaign.

591
00:29:09,280 --> 00:29:14,040
Are you upset? It will be okay.

592
00:29:14,680 --> 00:29:15,680
You're so dead.

593
00:29:16,560 --> 00:29:17,680
Totally dead, Off.

594
00:29:19,360 --> 00:29:20,880
I won't!

595
00:29:47,280 --> 00:29:52,440
My team and I are more than ready today.
We won't lose a third time.

596
00:29:53,800 --> 00:29:55,800
I'm not afraid. No matter what campaign.

597
00:29:55,880 --> 00:29:57,160
Hello, everyone.

598
00:29:57,240 --> 00:29:58,520
- Hello.
- Hello.

599
00:29:58,600 --> 00:30:02,160
Today, we're at
the Kantana Virtual Production Studio,

600
00:30:02,240 --> 00:30:05,480
the answer to all creative imagination.

601
00:30:05,560 --> 00:30:07,720
And you'll be facing

602
00:30:07,800 --> 00:30:11,160
a challenging runway
you've never seen before.

603
00:30:11,240 --> 00:30:15,600
Today's challenge has been
an iconic part of <i>The Face</i>

604
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:17,960
for the past ten years.

605
00:30:18,040 --> 00:30:21,000
A catwalk or what?
Bring it on, I'm ready to win.

606
00:30:21,080 --> 00:30:24,320
Please welcome the three mentors
to hear the brief together.

607
00:30:27,480 --> 00:30:30,720
Whether it's our daddy or mommy,
the others should be nervous.

608
00:30:31,320 --> 00:30:33,680
Because my daddy and mommy are the best.

609
00:30:33,760 --> 00:30:38,480
We can't lose today,
or Mile will be so upset.

610
00:30:38,560 --> 00:30:41,160
Today, we have a VIP guest

611
00:30:41,240 --> 00:30:45,000
with a major announcement for you all.

612
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:47,960
Please give a big hand for Cindy.

613
00:30:48,040 --> 00:30:49,560
SIRINYA BISHOP

614
00:30:49,640 --> 00:30:51,320
MODEL, ACTRESS, HOST,
AND WOMEN'S RIGHTS ACTIVIST

615
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:54,160
Wow, Cindy is so tall in person.

616
00:30:54,240 --> 00:30:57,000
Wow, is she a judge today?

617
00:30:57,080 --> 00:31:00,840
It's added pressure,
but we have to show her what we've got.

618
00:31:00,920 --> 00:31:04,160
Cindy, what's your announcement?

619
00:31:04,240 --> 00:31:07,920
Congratulations to everyone
still here on <i>The Face</i>.

620
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:11,480
To make the game a bit more fun,

621
00:31:11,560 --> 00:31:15,120
I'm here to announce a special rule.

622
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:17,160
Starting from this episode,

623
00:31:17,240 --> 00:31:21,600
the losing teams must send
at least one person

624
00:31:21,680 --> 00:31:23,560
to the Black Room.

625
00:31:23,640 --> 00:31:25,960
And the winning mentor

626
00:31:26,040 --> 00:31:31,000
has the right to eliminate
more than one person.

627
00:31:32,040 --> 00:31:36,240
That's just the show's usual dirty trick.

628
00:31:36,320 --> 00:31:38,400
It's to push us to win.

629
00:31:38,480 --> 00:31:41,160
The game is only going to get
more intense anyway.

630
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:42,800
Or…

631
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:44,840
they can choose to spare everyone.

632
00:31:44,920 --> 00:31:48,560
This rule takes effect
starting this episode.

633
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:50,000
Wait, I asked before.

634
00:31:50,080 --> 00:31:52,760
In the first one,
I asked to eliminate two.

635
00:31:52,840 --> 00:31:55,120
- It starts today. Are you deaf?
- It's before that.

636
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:58,520
So if I win, can I take back my request
and eliminate one more?

637
00:31:58,600 --> 00:31:59,440
No.

638
00:32:00,240 --> 00:32:03,760
Cindy just said it starts this week.

639
00:32:03,840 --> 00:32:06,680
- The past is past. Focus on now.
- Come here.

640
00:32:06,760 --> 00:32:09,920
- So you just make up the rules as you go?
- Lock in, man.

641
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:13,320
Like I said, this is <i>The Face</i>.
Anything can happen.

642
00:32:13,400 --> 00:32:15,000
It's not fair.

643
00:32:15,080 --> 00:32:19,320
It's not in the rule sheet.
You can't do that.

644
00:32:19,400 --> 00:32:22,280
We're focusing on the present
and doing our job today.

645
00:32:22,360 --> 00:32:23,400
Don't you get it?

646
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:26,080
Don't worry about me.
Just focus on your victory.

647
00:32:26,160 --> 00:32:28,560
Please welcome the person
with today's brief,

648
00:32:28,640 --> 00:32:31,040
Pongpisut Limgul, or Oab,

649
00:32:31,680 --> 00:32:35,320
Personal Care Commercial Lead
for Unilever Thailand, Cambodia, and Laos.

650
00:32:35,400 --> 00:32:38,520
Oab, what campaign do you have
for them today?

651
00:32:38,600 --> 00:32:40,480
Today's campaign

652
00:32:40,560 --> 00:32:43,680
is called "The Iconic Dining,
Presented by AXE."

653
00:32:43,760 --> 00:32:47,760
We'll be turning a dining table
into a runway.

654
00:32:47,840 --> 00:32:50,960
From a dining table to a runway.

655
00:32:51,040 --> 00:32:53,320
The iconic challenge
of <i>The Face </i>has returned.

656
00:32:53,400 --> 00:32:54,400
Give it up for that!

657
00:32:55,840 --> 00:32:57,040
Sounds like fun.

658
00:32:57,120 --> 00:32:59,480
The legendary dining-table runway.

659
00:32:59,560 --> 00:33:02,360
I want to make it legendary again.

660
00:33:02,440 --> 00:33:04,320
So much stuff on the table.

661
00:33:04,400 --> 00:33:06,200
I'll definitely break something.

662
00:33:06,280 --> 00:33:08,560
The runway is shaped like an X

663
00:33:08,640 --> 00:33:11,320
with many obstacles, so walking on it

664
00:33:11,400 --> 00:33:13,680
requires skill and creativity.

665
00:33:13,760 --> 00:33:15,960
It will push your boundaries,

666
00:33:16,040 --> 00:33:18,920
elevate your potential,
and force you to think outside the box.

667
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:22,160
Because we, AXE, want the contestants

668
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:26,360
to show their cool, stylish,
and confident side

669
00:33:26,440 --> 00:33:29,960
to match our Premium
Fine Fragrance Collection.

670
00:33:30,040 --> 00:33:34,000
It's all about cool guys
with a confident look.

671
00:33:34,080 --> 00:33:38,160
AXE has prepared AXE Blue Lavender
from the best-selling

672
00:33:38,240 --> 00:33:41,320
AXE Fine Fragrance Collection
for you to try.

673
00:33:41,400 --> 00:33:43,800
We collaborated with world-class perfumers

674
00:33:43,880 --> 00:33:46,280
to create an unexpectedly premium scent

675
00:33:46,360 --> 00:33:48,840
that offers 72-hour odor protection.

676
00:33:48,920 --> 00:33:50,480
But here's the catch.

677
00:33:50,560 --> 00:33:52,680
Before you step onto
the dining-table runway,

678
00:33:52,760 --> 00:33:55,160
we want you to spray AXE Blue Lavender

679
00:33:55,240 --> 00:33:57,680
to awaken your confidence and charm.

680
00:33:57,760 --> 00:34:00,240
In the show,
you have full creative freedom.

681
00:34:00,320 --> 00:34:02,240
Present the product however you like.

682
00:34:02,320 --> 00:34:05,800
Hold it or use it to fit
"The Iconic Dining" theme.

683
00:34:05,880 --> 00:34:10,199
Above all, the AXE men must look
cool, charming, and captivating.

684
00:34:10,280 --> 00:34:13,639
Any tips on how to spray it
to bring out its charm?

685
00:34:13,719 --> 00:34:16,239
You should spray AXE
in the shape of a seven.

686
00:34:16,320 --> 00:34:18,360
It covers the sweat zones

687
00:34:18,440 --> 00:34:22,920
to maximize the scent
of the Fine Fragrance Collection.

688
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:24,880
What a cool way to spray it.

689
00:34:31,920 --> 00:34:32,760
AXE.

690
00:34:32,840 --> 00:34:35,880
The winners of our recent master class,

691
00:34:35,960 --> 00:34:37,880
Pom and Mew, please come forward.

692
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:41,639
This is your special privilege.

693
00:34:41,719 --> 00:34:46,360
You get to choose which outfits
each team will wear

694
00:34:46,440 --> 00:34:47,760
for today's campaign.

695
00:34:47,840 --> 00:34:49,719
We have three brands today.

696
00:34:49,800 --> 00:34:52,880
The first brand in the middle is Sanitoro.

697
00:34:52,960 --> 00:34:56,800
It features rock-style clothing
with long skirts.

698
00:34:56,880 --> 00:35:00,280
The second brand is ANURUQ.

699
00:35:00,360 --> 00:35:03,280
It features pastel and black outfits

700
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:05,600
with floor-length coats.

701
00:35:05,680 --> 00:35:08,520
And the final brand over here
is La Boutique.

702
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:12,720
It features nude clothing
with tight corsets.

703
00:35:12,800 --> 00:35:17,120
The brands will also determine
your lineup order.

704
00:35:17,200 --> 00:35:19,520
So choose wisely.

705
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:21,840
Pom, I think ANURUQ suits your team.

706
00:35:21,920 --> 00:35:23,440
- Hey.
- Bright colors.

707
00:35:23,520 --> 00:35:25,240
I was just messing with them.

708
00:35:25,320 --> 00:35:26,440
Looking at the options,

709
00:35:27,240 --> 00:35:30,560
it's likely we'll get the fishtail outfits

710
00:35:30,640 --> 00:35:32,800
or the long, trailing coats.

711
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:36,160
I turned to Mew and Pom like,

712
00:35:36,240 --> 00:35:38,280
"I'm begging you. Please."

713
00:35:38,360 --> 00:35:40,040
It wouldn't hurt to be kind.

714
00:35:40,120 --> 00:35:41,680
Why not!

715
00:35:42,720 --> 00:35:46,320
But on the battlefield,
we don't know each other.

716
00:35:46,400 --> 00:35:48,160
You're on your own. Got it?

717
00:35:48,720 --> 00:35:50,800
Travis doesn't need friends.

718
00:35:51,680 --> 00:35:53,560
In addition, mentors,

719
00:35:53,640 --> 00:35:55,840
we have props.

720
00:35:55,920 --> 00:35:59,600
Each team must use every single prop.

721
00:35:59,680 --> 00:36:03,760
Time to decide. Which brand for your team?

722
00:36:03,840 --> 00:36:05,160
Pom…

723
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:07,960
I choose La Boutique.

724
00:36:08,040 --> 00:36:10,040
I'll challenge myself
with those high heels.

725
00:36:10,120 --> 00:36:13,000
We swam and dove last week.
This week, high heels.

726
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:18,320
High heels are usually for women,
but I can pull off anything.

727
00:36:18,400 --> 00:36:21,680
All right, which brand
for Mentor Mile's team?

728
00:36:21,760 --> 00:36:22,960
Please have ANURUQ.

729
00:36:23,040 --> 00:36:25,040
Yes, let's get it.

730
00:36:25,120 --> 00:36:29,440
I think it suits us best.
Mew is truly my little princess.

731
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:33,280
That means Mentor Mile's team gets ANURUQ.

732
00:36:33,360 --> 00:36:36,280
And Mentor Pancake's team gets Sanitoro.

733
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:39,360
All three mentors, please make your way

734
00:36:39,440 --> 00:36:41,480
to the performance order cards.

735
00:36:42,080 --> 00:36:44,320
If you're ready, reveal your cards.

736
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:46,760
Oh, wow.

737
00:36:48,600 --> 00:36:50,200
Going first

738
00:36:50,280 --> 00:36:53,240
is challenging
due to less preparation time.

739
00:36:53,320 --> 00:36:57,720
It's fine. We'll make the most
of what we have.

740
00:36:57,800 --> 00:36:59,640
Everyone, please go get ready.

741
00:37:01,760 --> 00:37:05,920
My team chose the most difficult outfits.

742
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:07,560
Two of them are wearing heels.

743
00:37:07,640 --> 00:37:10,240
But I believe they can do it.

744
00:37:10,320 --> 00:37:13,120
If they actually pull it off, I'll clap.

745
00:37:14,360 --> 00:37:15,880
Don't drop anything.

746
00:37:16,520 --> 00:37:18,320
- Hello.
- Hello.

747
00:37:18,400 --> 00:37:21,040
I brought a guest.
Don't start the time yet.

748
00:37:21,120 --> 00:37:25,120
I brought my sister this week.
She's going to help me win today.

749
00:37:25,200 --> 00:37:28,520
Hello, Madaew is here.

750
00:37:29,160 --> 00:37:30,200
For?

751
00:37:30,280 --> 00:37:31,720
For the victory!

752
00:37:31,800 --> 00:37:33,200
APICHET ATIRATTANA

753
00:37:33,280 --> 00:37:35,760
Madaew is exactly what I expected.

754
00:37:35,840 --> 00:37:38,480
She has energy, creativity,
and most importantly,

755
00:37:38,560 --> 00:37:41,600
she's bold in her presentation.

756
00:37:41,680 --> 00:37:43,640
- Okay, hello again.
- Hello.

757
00:37:43,720 --> 00:37:45,480
- I'll dive into my questions.
- Okay.

758
00:37:45,560 --> 00:37:49,600
If we carry it on the runway, spray it,
and play with it to highlight the product,

759
00:37:49,680 --> 00:37:50,800
- Is that allowed?
- Sure.

760
00:37:50,880 --> 00:37:54,720
I don't mind, as long as the look
stays true to our brand's cool vibe.

761
00:37:54,800 --> 00:37:58,480
What if we add a grunge vibe
to make the walk look cooler?

762
00:37:58,560 --> 00:38:01,000
Sweeping things off the table?
Is that okay?

763
00:38:01,080 --> 00:38:03,800
That's fine for me.
You have full creative freedom.

764
00:38:03,880 --> 00:38:07,160
But the final image
must look cool and stylish.

765
00:38:07,240 --> 00:38:10,160
Will you be the only judge
making the final decision?

766
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:13,680
It will be decided by five judges,
and I'll be one of them.

767
00:38:13,760 --> 00:38:14,600
- Okay.
- All right.

768
00:38:14,680 --> 00:38:17,440
Coolness and rock vibe
can go hand in hand.

769
00:38:17,520 --> 00:38:20,360
Most importantly,
how do we sell the product?

770
00:38:20,440 --> 00:38:22,000
Let's take a look.

771
00:38:22,080 --> 00:38:22,920
- Hello.
- Hello.

772
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:24,960
What defines AXE men?

773
00:38:25,040 --> 00:38:31,320
AXE men are cool,
well-groomed, and confident.

774
00:38:31,400 --> 00:38:35,920
If they knock over glasses or small props,
will points be deducted?

775
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:39,280
We actually consider that an obstacle.

776
00:38:39,360 --> 00:38:40,360
- Okay.
- They should

777
00:38:40,440 --> 00:38:42,160
walk without hitting anything…

778
00:38:42,240 --> 00:38:45,600
Ultimately, we need to make it
more challenging.

779
00:38:45,680 --> 00:38:48,160
We want the contestants
to show their skills.

780
00:38:48,240 --> 00:38:49,720
How can they win?

781
00:38:49,800 --> 00:38:52,800
They need to represent our brand

782
00:38:52,880 --> 00:38:54,840
with their coolness and individuality.

783
00:38:55,440 --> 00:38:58,880
They want a fashion show,
but I may add more theatrical elements.

784
00:38:58,960 --> 00:39:01,320
To make it feel more like
a live performance.

785
00:39:01,400 --> 00:39:04,080
I'm confident my team will do great.

786
00:39:05,040 --> 00:39:06,320
Okay, five minutes.

787
00:39:06,400 --> 00:39:08,200
Have you started the timer?

788
00:39:08,280 --> 00:39:13,200
First question. How should they feel
after spraying it?

789
00:39:13,280 --> 00:39:17,360
I want them to feel cool, confident,
and true to themselves.

790
00:39:17,440 --> 00:39:19,520
They can interpret that however they like.

791
00:39:19,600 --> 00:39:22,280
But that's the message
we want to convey today.

792
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:25,360
Do you have any expectations
for the finale of my team?

793
00:39:25,440 --> 00:39:28,840
Honestly, Off, you can interpret

794
00:39:28,920 --> 00:39:31,960
- and present it however you see fit.
- All right.

795
00:39:32,040 --> 00:39:34,640
So I can add any storyline to it?

796
00:39:34,720 --> 00:39:36,120
- Yes.
- But not weird.

797
00:39:36,200 --> 00:39:37,960
- Right. Don't make it weird.
- Okay.

798
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:40,560
Last question. Can I walk up there?

799
00:39:40,640 --> 00:39:42,920
Go for it.
Do your best within the time limit.

800
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:45,240
Two minutes left.

801
00:39:45,320 --> 00:39:47,600
Relax. I'm out of questions.

802
00:39:47,680 --> 00:39:49,680
Ultimately, they just want three things.

803
00:39:49,760 --> 00:39:53,360
To be cool, authentic, and creative.
But I'm doing this alone.

804
00:39:53,440 --> 00:39:55,280
If I win, I think…

805
00:39:55,920 --> 00:39:58,440
no one can accuse me of cheating anymore.

806
00:39:58,520 --> 00:40:01,120
- Hello.
- Hello. Close your eyes.

807
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:04,320
Let's try an exercise.
Take a deep breath for five seconds.

808
00:40:04,400 --> 00:40:08,840
One, two, three, four, five.
Now, exhale slowly.

809
00:40:08,920 --> 00:40:10,360
Say that you're a fighter.

810
00:40:10,440 --> 00:40:13,760
- Fighter!
- Fighter!

811
00:40:13,840 --> 00:40:15,800
Open your eyes. Let's go.

812
00:40:15,880 --> 00:40:17,360
I brought an assistant today.

813
00:40:17,440 --> 00:40:21,880
I was surprised Mile brought Madaew.
I'm a huge fan of her work.

814
00:40:21,960 --> 00:40:26,360
Because she's incredibly creative
and quick on her feet. I like that.

815
00:40:26,440 --> 00:40:28,160
For the opening, we'll go wild.

816
00:40:28,240 --> 00:40:30,560
We'll start by destroying
everything on set.

817
00:40:30,640 --> 00:40:33,960
We already had a plan,
but theirs is way better.

818
00:40:34,040 --> 00:40:35,800
It really hits the mark.

819
00:40:35,880 --> 00:40:38,160
The key isn't just about destroying props.

820
00:40:38,240 --> 00:40:40,960
We show that the obstacles
in front of us aren't a problem.

821
00:40:41,040 --> 00:40:44,320
You're already cool,
composed, and captivating.

822
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:46,080
Your goal is right ahead of you.

823
00:40:46,160 --> 00:40:47,360
Right.

824
00:40:47,440 --> 00:40:49,920
Time is short.
We have to manage it strictly.

825
00:40:50,000 --> 00:40:53,480
The first two minutes are to teach them
how to walk in character.

826
00:40:53,560 --> 00:40:55,000
Let's check out the outfits.

827
00:40:55,080 --> 00:40:57,400
We'll sort out the blocking on set.

828
00:40:57,480 --> 00:41:00,600
Check the outfits first, okay?
The outfits are confusing.

829
00:41:00,680 --> 00:41:02,960
They added extra layers,
so we have to adapt.

830
00:41:03,040 --> 00:41:06,320
I need to make them work for our guys.

831
00:41:06,400 --> 00:41:09,160
I'm short, so we agreed
I wouldn't wear anything long.

832
00:41:09,240 --> 00:41:10,800
But I got the longest outfit.

833
00:41:11,400 --> 00:41:15,120
It's way too long.
I don't know what to do.

834
00:41:17,800 --> 00:41:20,160
- Hello.
- Hello.

835
00:41:20,240 --> 00:41:25,880
Today, AXE is looking for someone
cool, confident, and authentic.

836
00:41:25,960 --> 00:41:28,520
The team pulled itself together
very quickly.

837
00:41:28,600 --> 00:41:31,000
And they have their own creative ideas.

838
00:41:31,080 --> 00:41:34,200
Beyond my brief,
it seems like they already have…

839
00:41:34,280 --> 00:41:35,880
a clear vision in mind.

840
00:41:35,960 --> 00:41:38,680
I want everyone to walk
in all four directions.

841
00:41:38,760 --> 00:41:41,200
And return to the starting point.

842
00:41:41,280 --> 00:41:43,680
This actually requires a lot of teamwork.

843
00:41:43,760 --> 00:41:47,720
The pattern seems simple,
but it's hard to pull off.

844
00:41:47,800 --> 00:41:52,720
While walking, you need to keep
a constant rhythm.

845
00:41:52,800 --> 00:41:55,720
But I also want your characters
to show on your faces.

846
00:41:55,800 --> 00:41:59,520
I'm just worried
there will be too much action.

847
00:41:59,600 --> 00:42:02,640
If everyone is doing an action sequence
on both sides…

848
00:42:02,720 --> 00:42:05,280
- Interacting with props…
- It will be too much.

849
00:42:05,360 --> 00:42:07,320
Keep it sharp and focused.

850
00:42:07,400 --> 00:42:09,200
It's fine for a fashion show.

851
00:42:09,280 --> 00:42:12,240
But since we're adding
theatrical elements,

852
00:42:12,320 --> 00:42:16,640
I want Ananda to help bring out
their coolness, confidence,

853
00:42:16,720 --> 00:42:19,200
and sexiness in everyone's characters.

854
00:42:19,280 --> 00:42:20,920
We'll be working closely on this.

855
00:42:21,000 --> 00:42:25,840
Two, three, four. One, two, three, four.

856
00:42:25,920 --> 00:42:29,760
One, two, three, four, five.

857
00:42:29,840 --> 00:42:31,640
I think PP was struggling a bit.

858
00:42:31,720 --> 00:42:34,680
PP was struggling
with the pace and the starting cue.

859
00:42:34,760 --> 00:42:38,960
He can't quite catch
the drumbeats and bass kicks.

860
00:42:39,520 --> 00:42:43,040
If you listen closely, there's a beat,
then a slight pause.

861
00:42:43,120 --> 00:42:45,360
- Yes.
- Before the drop.

862
00:42:45,440 --> 00:42:47,680
It's not hard to time it.
Focus on the music.

863
00:42:50,440 --> 00:42:52,160
Hear it? No need to step heavily.

864
00:42:52,240 --> 00:42:53,560
- Just listen.
- Yes.

865
00:42:53,640 --> 00:42:55,680
If I count carefully, I can hear it too.

866
00:42:55,760 --> 00:42:56,680
- Yes.
- Yes.

867
00:42:56,760 --> 00:42:58,760
Too much advice just makes me panic.

868
00:42:58,840 --> 00:43:00,840
It makes me nervous. I mean…

869
00:43:00,920 --> 00:43:03,240
Like this, this, this…

870
00:43:04,560 --> 00:43:07,600
It's like I'm wearing earphones

871
00:43:08,480 --> 00:43:11,200
with ten songs playing at once.
Who could understand that?

872
00:43:11,280 --> 00:43:12,720
Listen to a long version, so…

873
00:43:12,800 --> 00:43:14,880
- Long version.
- Where the song changes.

874
00:43:14,960 --> 00:43:15,800
One minute.

875
00:43:15,880 --> 00:43:19,000
I meditated earlier
to reflect on my mistakes.

876
00:43:19,080 --> 00:43:23,080
I tried to take
everyone's input and adjust.

877
00:43:24,000 --> 00:43:28,000
I'm ready and feeling better now.
The makeup will do the rest.

878
00:43:29,160 --> 00:43:30,000
Wait.

879
00:43:31,040 --> 00:43:31,880
Hey.

880
00:43:31,960 --> 00:43:33,720
Come on, guys.

881
00:43:34,760 --> 00:43:37,920
Okay, I'm here alone today,
so let's help each other.

882
00:43:38,000 --> 00:43:39,360
First of all…

883
00:43:40,520 --> 00:43:43,520
- Focus, because I really want to win.
- Understood.

884
00:43:43,600 --> 00:43:47,920
Other teams have assistants,
but if we win, that will shut them up.

885
00:43:48,720 --> 00:43:51,120
- First, let's pick our outfits.
- Let's start.

886
00:43:51,800 --> 00:43:53,840
Who's wearing what?

887
00:43:53,920 --> 00:43:55,920
Hearing that fired me up. I felt…

888
00:43:56,000 --> 00:43:57,960
A voice in my head said,

889
00:43:58,040 --> 00:44:00,280
"Look, Off is our only mentor today.

890
00:44:00,360 --> 00:44:02,960
Just wait and see what happens if we win."

891
00:44:04,280 --> 00:44:06,440
Honestly, Off didn't even need to come.

892
00:44:06,520 --> 00:44:07,880
We got this.

893
00:44:07,960 --> 00:44:10,520
Change into your shoes.
I'll show you the pattern.

894
00:44:11,480 --> 00:44:13,040
I just came up with a pattern.

895
00:44:13,120 --> 00:44:15,640
I showed them the pattern
in these ten minutes.

896
00:44:15,720 --> 00:44:17,240
Because it's hard to memorize.

897
00:44:17,320 --> 00:44:19,560
Before they tested the runway,

898
00:44:19,640 --> 00:44:21,160
they learned the pattern.

899
00:44:21,240 --> 00:44:24,440
They can review it anytime
because the pattern is already set.

900
00:44:24,520 --> 00:44:26,800
After the pose, one, two, one, two.

901
00:44:27,400 --> 00:44:31,400
Go. Lead. Walk, walk, walk.

902
00:44:31,480 --> 00:44:35,520
The pattern Off gave us today?
I don't think it's hard, but…

903
00:44:35,600 --> 00:44:39,320
I think memorizing it and letting it flow…

904
00:44:39,400 --> 00:44:42,240
If we make a mistake, don't show it.

905
00:44:43,720 --> 00:44:46,120
- One, two, three, four.
- Separate.

906
00:44:46,200 --> 00:44:48,400
- Mew, go back the same way.
- The same way.

907
00:44:48,480 --> 00:44:50,400
I'm most worried about Mew.

908
00:44:50,480 --> 00:44:54,320
Maybe he easily loses focus

909
00:44:54,400 --> 00:44:56,920
so he's distracted by too many things.

910
00:44:57,000 --> 00:44:59,280
He's the slowest to memorize.

911
00:45:01,040 --> 00:45:02,200
That's it.

912
00:45:02,280 --> 00:45:03,160
Go. Separate.

913
00:45:04,880 --> 00:45:05,720
Okay.

914
00:45:05,800 --> 00:45:08,800
- Mew, you have to lock eyes with me.
- Yes.

915
00:45:08,880 --> 00:45:12,240
Mew got a warning from Pom.
That's good, they're a team.

916
00:45:12,320 --> 00:45:13,440
They move together.

917
00:45:13,520 --> 00:45:16,840
Okay, we're short on time.
I've divided this into three parts.

918
00:45:16,920 --> 00:45:19,480
First, we'll block the positions.

919
00:45:19,560 --> 00:45:21,560
We plan to have three parts.

920
00:45:21,640 --> 00:45:23,120
Five minutes of blocking.

921
00:45:23,200 --> 00:45:25,480
Just do the blocking,
don't break anything yet.

922
00:45:25,560 --> 00:45:28,240
A five-minute break, then we run the cues.

923
00:45:28,320 --> 00:45:31,960
It wasn't that easy on stage.
We only had time for two practice runs.

924
00:45:32,040 --> 00:45:34,400
The first run was blocking,
which is important.

925
00:45:34,480 --> 00:45:36,400
Three, two, one, walk.

926
00:45:36,480 --> 00:45:37,400
Go.

927
00:45:38,240 --> 00:45:40,880
- Stop. Did you forget to spray it?
- I already sprayed.

928
00:45:40,960 --> 00:45:42,760
I want to see it. One more time.

929
00:45:42,840 --> 00:45:43,680
One more time.

930
00:45:43,760 --> 00:45:46,360
We want a grunge, rock vibe.

931
00:45:46,440 --> 00:45:49,000
It needs to be fierce, like a Gen Z kid.

932
00:45:49,640 --> 00:45:52,680
The walk has to be reserved.
You should avoid eye contact.

933
00:45:52,760 --> 00:45:54,760
Show that you're holding back.

934
00:45:54,840 --> 00:45:57,040
Yeah, that's it.

935
00:45:57,120 --> 00:45:59,360
Peem was definitely the star.

936
00:45:59,440 --> 00:46:01,480
He understood exactly what style I wanted.

937
00:46:01,560 --> 00:46:02,840
He was the most accurate.

938
00:46:02,920 --> 00:46:05,960
But the one I'm worried about is Leo.

939
00:46:06,040 --> 00:46:11,320
He said he would walk like a gangster,
but I don't see that at all.

940
00:46:11,400 --> 00:46:13,800
Go. Serve some attitude.

941
00:46:14,800 --> 00:46:16,360
Right. Spray seven.

942
00:46:17,000 --> 00:46:18,840
Right, don't break it. Right.

943
00:46:19,600 --> 00:46:23,440
My show has three parts.
It's a shame we couldn't

944
00:46:23,520 --> 00:46:27,840
make it happen with a pure grunge concept.

945
00:46:27,920 --> 00:46:33,400
Because there were safety concerns
for the guests.

946
00:46:33,480 --> 00:46:34,640
So we had to scrap it.

947
00:46:35,200 --> 00:46:36,800
We had to rethink our plan.

948
00:46:36,880 --> 00:46:40,680
We needed to adjust our strategy
to make it more appropriate.

949
00:46:40,760 --> 00:46:43,600
Or else Pancake
won't have any glasses left for her team.

950
00:46:45,240 --> 00:46:46,960
- Go ahead.
- Thank you.

951
00:46:47,040 --> 00:46:48,640
Go change your clothes.

952
00:46:48,720 --> 00:46:52,000
Everyone is focused.
We just need to build up the energy.

953
00:46:52,640 --> 00:46:55,240
I think for our show,

954
00:46:55,320 --> 00:46:57,840
we'll start with the members
at the AXE station.

955
00:46:57,920 --> 00:47:01,000
Then we start with a heavy beat, and…

956
00:47:02,080 --> 00:47:03,200
spray it.

957
00:47:07,240 --> 00:47:10,000
I'm 90% sure.

958
00:47:10,080 --> 00:47:14,520
I like how we practice,
talk, and care for each other.

959
00:47:14,600 --> 00:47:17,080
We're on the same page and in sync.

960
00:47:17,160 --> 00:47:22,360
My outfit has this long piece of fabric.

961
00:47:22,440 --> 00:47:25,840
I need to be prepared
because everything depends on me.

962
00:47:25,920 --> 00:47:31,080
I'll try it out first to see
what works on the real stage.

963
00:47:31,160 --> 00:47:33,720
- Should it sweep the floor?
- It's a point deduction.

964
00:47:33,800 --> 00:47:35,680
- Who dropped the candlestick?
- I did.

965
00:47:35,760 --> 00:47:37,640
My skirt dragged everything down.

966
00:47:37,720 --> 00:47:40,920
It dragged down everything.
Everything fell off the table.

967
00:47:41,000 --> 00:47:43,160
I would've done better without this skirt.

968
00:47:43,240 --> 00:47:44,560
- How should I?
- Hold it up?

969
00:47:44,640 --> 00:47:45,880
- Fine.
- I'm worried.

970
00:47:45,960 --> 00:47:50,120
Kimhan looked worried, so I said,

971
00:47:50,200 --> 00:47:53,200
"If you have to wear it, just hold it up."

972
00:47:53,280 --> 00:47:56,760
Just do whatever you want.
Sometimes you're caught in the middle…

973
00:47:56,840 --> 00:47:58,320
Let's walk.

974
00:47:58,400 --> 00:48:00,200
It's just practice.

975
00:48:00,280 --> 00:48:02,640
I wanted to save my energy.

976
00:48:02,720 --> 00:48:07,120
Come on. If I ask you to do it
a hundred times, you should do it.

977
00:48:07,200 --> 00:48:10,120
Yes. When I walk, everyone will see
the real AXE man.

978
00:48:11,840 --> 00:48:14,320
Okay, come on. It's our time.

979
00:48:14,400 --> 00:48:16,240
- Keep fighting.
- Let's get it.

980
00:48:16,320 --> 00:48:17,880
- Confident and cool.
- I am.

981
00:48:17,960 --> 00:48:19,440
Come on, let's bring it in.

982
00:48:19,520 --> 00:48:21,520
- One, two, three.
- Let's get it!

983
00:48:22,720 --> 00:48:24,440
Wearing heels was hard

984
00:48:24,520 --> 00:48:27,040
because I've never modeled
in heels before.

985
00:48:27,120 --> 00:48:29,600
But when I tried them on and walked,
it was okay.

986
00:48:29,680 --> 00:48:32,040
I did fall a few times during practice.

987
00:48:32,120 --> 00:48:33,680
Mew, walk up on that side.

988
00:48:34,240 --> 00:48:35,280
Hype up the audience.

989
00:48:35,360 --> 00:48:36,200
Don't rush.

990
00:48:36,280 --> 00:48:37,520
Crap, don't rush.

991
00:48:37,600 --> 00:48:38,880
That's okay.

992
00:48:38,960 --> 00:48:43,320
It hurts, but the outfits
won't stop Team Off.

993
00:48:43,400 --> 00:48:44,920
Team Off relies on teamwork.

994
00:48:45,000 --> 00:48:46,560
Bring on the outfits.

995
00:48:46,640 --> 00:48:49,000
Even if it's eight meters long,
bring it on.

996
00:48:49,080 --> 00:48:49,960
And don't forget.

997
00:48:50,040 --> 00:48:51,720
- Grab the product…
- And spray.

998
00:48:51,800 --> 00:48:53,960
Watch him. When he sprays, you kneel.

999
00:48:54,040 --> 00:48:55,480
Nine.

1000
00:48:55,560 --> 00:48:56,480
Eight.

1001
00:48:56,560 --> 00:48:59,200
This is as far as I can guide them.

1002
00:48:59,280 --> 00:49:03,440
I gave them my all. Now, it's up to them.

1003
00:49:03,520 --> 00:49:07,680
I want them to be themselves.
Be cool in the AXE way.

1004
00:49:07,760 --> 00:49:09,080
That's all there is to it.

1005
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:11,880
- Hello.
- Hey.

1006
00:49:11,960 --> 00:49:14,320
First, let me introduce my little sister.

1007
00:49:14,400 --> 00:49:17,400
Mile brought a helper.
Finally playing the game?

1008
00:49:17,480 --> 00:49:22,560
We'll definitely
see some humor and creativity.

1009
00:49:22,640 --> 00:49:25,920
Hold on. I remember last week,

1010
00:49:26,000 --> 00:49:30,440
Mentor Mile challenged Mentor Off
to guide the campaign alone.

1011
00:49:30,520 --> 00:49:33,200
- But I told him…
- Wow, someone can't keep a promise.

1012
00:49:33,280 --> 00:49:37,480
Wait, hold on. I told him in his IG DMs.

1013
00:49:37,560 --> 00:49:40,280
"I'm bringing a helper tomorrow.
Just a heads-up."

1014
00:49:40,360 --> 00:49:43,720
We smiled with good intentions.

1015
00:49:43,800 --> 00:49:46,680
You did your homework by inviting someone.
Very prepared.

1016
00:49:46,760 --> 00:49:49,160
But don't expect me to be okay with it.

1017
00:49:49,240 --> 00:49:50,280
Mile.

1018
00:49:50,360 --> 00:49:51,960
You've been planning this.

1019
00:49:52,040 --> 00:49:53,640
And you only just told me.

1020
00:49:53,720 --> 00:49:55,160
You saw it last night?

1021
00:49:55,240 --> 00:49:56,760
It was already late when I saw.

1022
00:49:56,840 --> 00:49:58,840
- Really? Is that true?
- You planned it.

1023
00:49:58,920 --> 00:50:02,480
How was I supposed to find someone?
The celebs at my agency are busy.

1024
00:50:02,560 --> 00:50:04,240
You have to tell me in advance.

1025
00:50:04,320 --> 00:50:06,240
You're just making excuses.

1026
00:50:06,320 --> 00:50:09,360
Out of 170 celebrities,
you couldn't book a single one?

1027
00:50:09,440 --> 00:50:13,600
All right. I believe all the mentors
are ready now. Let's begin.

1028
00:50:13,680 --> 00:50:19,040
Okay, based on Pancake's idea earlier,
she wants everyone to…

1029
00:50:19,120 --> 00:50:22,080
line up by teams one, two, and three.

1030
00:50:22,160 --> 00:50:26,240
Pancake already has a pattern.
I was just helping her organize it.

1031
00:50:26,320 --> 00:50:28,440
Team One lines up first.
Then the rest respectively.

1032
00:50:28,520 --> 00:50:31,120
That's what I planned.
Once everyone walks out,

1033
00:50:31,200 --> 00:50:35,600
I don't want to complicate the ending.
Just keep it clean and visible.

1034
00:50:35,680 --> 00:50:39,680
They pose, and everyone is visible.
I think that's enough.

1035
00:50:39,760 --> 00:50:42,400
When you're ready, walk up.

1036
00:50:42,480 --> 00:50:46,640
Then cross. When you cross paths,
just stagger it. Okay.

1037
00:50:46,720 --> 00:50:50,280
Pancake is so professional.
When she counts down,

1038
00:50:50,360 --> 00:50:52,400
it happens exactly as she says.

1039
00:50:52,480 --> 00:50:55,800
Do you want them to turn differently?

1040
00:50:55,880 --> 00:50:58,320
Good. Off, help me check from up there.

1041
00:50:58,400 --> 00:51:02,000
Everything was perfect.
So I asked if I could try something.

1042
00:51:02,080 --> 00:51:03,440
Want to adjust anything?

1043
00:51:03,520 --> 00:51:04,920
- Can I add something?
- Go.

1044
00:51:05,000 --> 00:51:07,280
- It's a bit lacking.
- Too short, right?

1045
00:51:07,360 --> 00:51:08,720
- Yes.
- Okay.

1046
00:51:08,800 --> 00:51:12,360
Can they try walking the entire perimeter?
Covering every corner?

1047
00:51:12,440 --> 00:51:14,880
But it didn't look good.

1048
00:51:14,960 --> 00:51:15,800
I gave up.

1049
00:51:15,880 --> 00:51:19,320
I had to apologize to everyone
because I wasted their time.

1050
00:51:19,400 --> 00:51:22,960
Stop practicing. Walk in an X shape,
like the first time, remember?

1051
00:51:23,040 --> 00:51:25,440
Cross paths.
Wherever you stop, stay right there.

1052
00:51:25,520 --> 00:51:28,160
- Keep the same pattern.
- Keeping it simple is better.

1053
00:51:29,880 --> 00:51:31,320
But Mile didn't say anything.

1054
00:51:31,400 --> 00:51:35,000
Working as a team,
I can step back and let others lead.

1055
00:51:35,080 --> 00:51:39,280
Mile, just enjoy not making decisions.
Just say yes or no, like a CEO.

1056
00:51:45,080 --> 00:51:48,440
Welcome back to our campaign,
The Iconic Dining Presented by AXE.

1057
00:51:48,520 --> 00:51:53,120
Let's welcome the judges
who will be evaluating today's campaign.

1058
00:51:53,200 --> 00:51:54,840
Give a big round of applause

1059
00:51:54,920 --> 00:51:56,640
for Master Mentor Adam and Cindy.

1060
00:52:04,520 --> 00:52:06,480
M.R. CHALERMCHATRI YUKOL

1061
00:52:06,560 --> 00:52:08,240
CINDY
SIRINYA BISHOP

1062
00:52:08,320 --> 00:52:12,000
Our next two judges,
Royal Mom and Ma Ornapa.

1063
00:52:13,960 --> 00:52:15,680
APIWAT YOSPRAPAN

1064
00:52:15,760 --> 00:52:17,080
ORNAPA KRISADEE

1065
00:52:17,160 --> 00:52:21,160
And of course, today's campaign
wouldn't be complete

1066
00:52:21,240 --> 00:52:23,000
without our VIP guests.

1067
00:52:23,600 --> 00:52:26,520
Thailand's top-tier
celebrity fashion icons

1068
00:52:26,600 --> 00:52:29,320
and <i>The Face</i>'s warm family!

1069
00:52:29,400 --> 00:52:31,760
Today, our guests

1070
00:52:31,840 --> 00:52:35,680
have the special privilege
of voting for their favorite contestant

1071
00:52:35,760 --> 00:52:37,960
to win the Popular Vote award.

1072
00:52:38,040 --> 00:52:40,200
And the winner of the Popular Vote

1073
00:52:40,280 --> 00:52:44,480
will receive immunity
from the Black Room today.

1074
00:52:46,840 --> 00:52:48,520
I believe everyone is ready.

1075
00:52:48,600 --> 00:52:50,040
Let's watch the campaign,

1076
00:52:50,120 --> 00:52:52,720
The Iconic Dining Presented by AXE.

1077
00:52:54,920 --> 00:52:56,520
Team Mentor Mile.

1078
00:53:00,640 --> 00:53:01,840
The first one looks good.

1079
00:53:02,680 --> 00:53:03,720
Right?

1080
00:53:05,840 --> 00:53:07,480
Today is a runway walk.

1081
00:53:07,560 --> 00:53:12,960
The concept is about perfume users
radiating absolute confidence.

1082
00:53:13,040 --> 00:53:16,160
It's that rock vibe
coming to life right before our eyes.

1083
00:53:19,560 --> 00:53:22,240
I told the members
to tune in before walking out.

1084
00:53:22,320 --> 00:53:24,800
Focus, so the performance
flows seamlessly.

1085
00:53:30,320 --> 00:53:34,640
Team Mile was spectacular.
They walked out from four directions.

1086
00:53:37,360 --> 00:53:41,360
This step is tricky.
Going down is fine, but climbing up…

1087
00:53:45,040 --> 00:53:48,960
Opening the show is a huge honor.
I'm glad Mile let me go first.

1088
00:53:51,240 --> 00:53:52,640
Turn around!

1089
00:53:52,720 --> 00:53:54,960
I need to be cool and stylish.

1090
00:53:55,040 --> 00:53:58,160
The vibe of a rogue high school kid.

1091
00:53:58,240 --> 00:53:59,760
This is my place.

1092
00:54:01,240 --> 00:54:04,200
Team Milestone.
I'm serious. I'm not here to play around.

1093
00:54:06,560 --> 00:54:08,080
Looks on theme.

1094
00:54:08,160 --> 00:54:09,160
Peem did a good job.

1095
00:54:09,240 --> 00:54:11,800
But I feel like Peem could've done better.

1096
00:54:11,880 --> 00:54:16,400
Everyone on his team looks capable.
Mile has nothing to worry about.

1097
00:54:20,160 --> 00:54:22,200
I'm worried about Gluf.

1098
00:54:23,280 --> 00:54:27,200
Why walk out holding a guitar like that?
I don't get it. No one gets it.

1099
00:54:27,280 --> 00:54:29,640
The way he held it confused me.

1100
00:54:32,440 --> 00:54:34,640
It's such a shame,
because I'm a guitarist.

1101
00:54:34,720 --> 00:54:37,760
There's so much more you can do with it
than just hold it.

1102
00:54:37,840 --> 00:54:40,960
He didn't make a special choice.

1103
00:54:41,040 --> 00:54:44,720
It needs to be more grunge.
Glass should've broken from the start.

1104
00:54:44,800 --> 00:54:47,520
I wanted that vibe,
sweeping everything into the middle.

1105
00:54:47,600 --> 00:54:50,720
During practice,
everything was scattered and messy.

1106
00:54:50,800 --> 00:54:53,080
Go. Serve some attitude.

1107
00:54:53,160 --> 00:54:54,360
Right. Spray seven.

1108
00:54:54,440 --> 00:54:57,000
Right, don't break it. Right.

1109
00:54:57,080 --> 00:55:00,080
Madaew gave the idea
to just show up and sweep everything.

1110
00:55:00,160 --> 00:55:02,040
And I agreed it needed to be grunge.

1111
00:55:04,680 --> 00:55:06,640
That's it. Fabulous.

1112
00:55:06,720 --> 00:55:09,040
Whatever it was
that went against the concept

1113
00:55:09,120 --> 00:55:10,280
was changed.

1114
00:55:10,360 --> 00:55:11,960
They had to adjust again.

1115
00:55:12,040 --> 00:55:13,360
It made things harder.

1116
00:55:13,440 --> 00:55:14,360
Such a shame.

1117
00:55:14,440 --> 00:55:15,800
Break the glasses?

1118
00:55:15,880 --> 00:55:18,040
The glasses are an obstacle.

1119
00:55:18,120 --> 00:55:19,720
We can't go off script.

1120
00:55:19,800 --> 00:55:22,680
Because there are many other things
we have to consider.

1121
00:55:22,760 --> 00:55:25,400
I wanted an edgy, grunge vibe.
Something like that.

1122
00:55:25,480 --> 00:55:28,000
First of all, you have to worry
about the audience.

1123
00:55:28,080 --> 00:55:29,520
It's good Mile didn't do it.

1124
00:55:29,600 --> 00:55:33,840
I just wanted to create
a magical moment, that's all.

1125
00:55:33,920 --> 00:55:36,520
Breaking the glasses won't kill anyone.
I've done it.

1126
00:55:39,960 --> 00:55:42,040
I thought Jacob looked good.

1127
00:55:42,120 --> 00:55:44,960
Jacob is handsome.
And in that pink outfit, I must say…

1128
00:55:45,040 --> 00:55:46,280
he's very elegant.

1129
00:55:47,240 --> 00:55:49,640
It gave off an Elvis Presley vibe,

1130
00:55:53,040 --> 00:55:55,840
so I expected the energy to be better.

1131
00:55:55,920 --> 00:55:58,120
- He's walking with his head down.
- Yes.

1132
00:55:59,920 --> 00:56:02,360
I don't know what he's worried about.

1133
00:56:02,440 --> 00:56:05,840
I wasn't sure why he's looking
at the floor. I didn't get that.

1134
00:56:07,320 --> 00:56:11,160
He can't handle this outfit yet.
It made him anxious.

1135
00:56:11,240 --> 00:56:12,440
Yes, I noticed it too.

1136
00:56:12,520 --> 00:56:15,760
His focus was on his fear
of making mistakes.

1137
00:56:15,840 --> 00:56:16,840
Not blaming anyone.

1138
00:56:16,920 --> 00:56:19,440
If he couldn't pull it off,
then it was my fault.

1139
00:56:20,680 --> 00:56:22,080
It's my turn now.

1140
00:56:23,120 --> 00:56:25,360
I wanted to walk in
and embody the character.

1141
00:56:25,440 --> 00:56:26,520
And present myself.

1142
00:56:27,120 --> 00:56:29,360
He looked so good.

1143
00:56:29,440 --> 00:56:31,920
Manyoo changed a lot after the Black Room.

1144
00:56:32,000 --> 00:56:35,200
He had more intention. He fought harder.

1145
00:56:35,280 --> 00:56:38,720
This is okay, but one side looks robotic.

1146
00:56:38,800 --> 00:56:41,000
It's like he's always holding something.

1147
00:56:41,080 --> 00:56:42,960
I didn't mind the people on the side.

1148
00:56:43,040 --> 00:56:45,440
I just cared about moving forward.

1149
00:56:45,520 --> 00:56:48,240
I'm going to walk as fiercely as I can.

1150
00:56:52,840 --> 00:56:54,360
Oh, they fell everywhere.

1151
00:56:54,440 --> 00:56:55,720
It's all the way here.

1152
00:56:55,800 --> 00:56:57,800
- A minor accident.
- An accident.

1153
00:56:57,880 --> 00:57:00,840
If the glasses fell but his stride
didn't break, he pulled it off.

1154
00:57:00,920 --> 00:57:04,080
Having some mistakes is acceptable.

1155
00:57:10,680 --> 00:57:11,520
Fabulous!

1156
00:57:11,600 --> 00:57:13,280
So many people.

1157
00:57:13,360 --> 00:57:14,400
So many people.

1158
00:57:14,480 --> 00:57:16,160
I felt good. It was new to me.

1159
00:57:17,760 --> 00:57:20,200
I think Leo did better than in practice

1160
00:57:20,280 --> 00:57:22,880
because he really brought
his inner confidence out.

1161
00:57:23,560 --> 00:57:26,560
Very strong <i>Oppa </i>vibe. He's ripped.

1162
00:57:26,640 --> 00:57:28,880
Leo looked worried, but it didn't matter.

1163
00:57:28,960 --> 00:57:33,520
He was hesitating to act,
but did it anyway.

1164
00:57:33,600 --> 00:57:34,960
And he handled it well.

1165
00:57:36,520 --> 00:57:38,720
Peem carried the team a lot.

1166
00:57:38,800 --> 00:57:40,120
He got the most airtime.

1167
00:57:40,720 --> 00:57:43,440
The look, clothes, and hair.

1168
00:57:43,520 --> 00:57:44,720
Everything elevated him.

1169
00:57:46,280 --> 00:57:47,480
That's it.

1170
00:57:47,560 --> 00:57:49,640
- So edgy.
- Very good.

1171
00:57:49,720 --> 00:57:51,440
I like Peem's energy.

1172
00:57:51,520 --> 00:57:53,400
I have to give it to Peem.

1173
00:57:53,480 --> 00:57:57,120
He must pass this energy
to the rest of Mile's team.

1174
00:57:57,200 --> 00:58:01,120
He did well.
It was diverse and unexpected.

1175
00:58:01,200 --> 00:58:03,800
I presented various characters

1176
00:58:03,880 --> 00:58:07,600
because I want people to know that AXE
suits many different characters.

1177
00:58:11,240 --> 00:58:14,760
I don't understand
why Gluf sprayed people. For fun?

1178
00:58:14,840 --> 00:58:15,920
For the thrill?

1179
00:58:16,800 --> 00:58:19,840
I also wondered,
are you even allowed to spray outwards?

1180
00:58:19,920 --> 00:58:24,040
Since the brief said to spray
like this, one, two, three.

1181
00:58:24,120 --> 00:58:27,160
If you're going to spray abstractly,
make it abstract.

1182
00:58:27,240 --> 00:58:29,360
Now, the scent is all over the room.

1183
00:58:29,440 --> 00:58:32,040
Mile's team answered the brief well.

1184
00:58:32,120 --> 00:58:35,760
It was rock, and a good balance
between rock and classy.

1185
00:58:35,840 --> 00:58:38,800
This campaign required us
to totally switch off our brains.

1186
00:58:40,320 --> 00:58:43,360
I only had to stand in the middle
and show my handsome face.

1187
00:58:43,440 --> 00:58:45,040
Have fun. Enjoy it.

1188
00:58:50,000 --> 00:58:52,000
I sprayed seven, the others sprayed two.

1189
00:58:52,080 --> 00:58:54,880
Because our AXE lasts up to 72 hours.

1190
00:58:57,320 --> 00:58:59,320
It's a bummer they totally bombed.

1191
00:58:59,400 --> 00:59:01,240
He was in the center.

1192
00:59:01,320 --> 00:59:03,960
He was the highlight.
He could've done anything.

1193
00:59:04,040 --> 00:59:07,120
If he just went for it.
But he was too stiff.

1194
00:59:11,000 --> 00:59:14,840
Where was Mile's finale?
Great opening, but what was the closing?

1195
00:59:14,920 --> 00:59:18,320
I'm a bit disappointed,
but some contestants did better.

1196
00:59:18,400 --> 00:59:20,000
I don't think we would win.

1197
00:59:20,080 --> 00:59:21,440
It's a gut feeling.

1198
00:59:21,520 --> 00:59:25,280
If it were the old me,
I might have felt really down.

1199
00:59:25,360 --> 00:59:27,000
But now, I have just accepted it.

1200
00:59:27,920 --> 00:59:31,080
If someone from our team
has to go to the Black Room,

1201
00:59:31,600 --> 00:59:33,800
I think it will be me.

1202
00:59:33,880 --> 00:59:36,200
Now, let's move on to the second team.

1203
00:59:36,280 --> 00:59:38,600
Please welcome Team Pancake-Ananda!

1204
00:59:45,640 --> 00:59:46,720
You got this.

1205
00:59:46,800 --> 00:59:49,640
Today's theme is handsome, cool, and edgy.

1206
00:59:49,720 --> 00:59:51,520
But with the rock element,

1207
00:59:51,600 --> 00:59:55,040
the heavy beat makes it
quite a challenge for them.

1208
00:59:55,120 --> 00:59:56,480
There's one member missing.

1209
00:59:56,560 --> 00:59:58,160
He already got eliminated.

1210
00:59:58,240 --> 01:00:01,640
Everyone got nervous with all the lights.

1211
01:00:01,720 --> 01:00:03,680
The whole atmosphere made us nervous.

1212
01:00:03,760 --> 01:00:05,560
We're totally ready today.

1213
01:00:10,360 --> 01:00:14,080
Our show kicks off by spraying AXE.

1214
01:00:14,840 --> 01:00:17,680
This Blue Lavender scent calms my nerves.

1215
01:00:17,760 --> 01:00:19,240
It's the scent of a winner.

1216
01:00:21,200 --> 01:00:23,800
I don't know what it is, but it's unique.

1217
01:00:23,880 --> 01:00:27,040
I've never worn a shirt like this.
It was new to me.

1218
01:00:27,120 --> 01:00:31,160
I love it. I feel completely in the zone,
and the hair helps.

1219
01:00:31,240 --> 01:00:33,560
So rock and roll. Super cool.

1220
01:00:36,320 --> 01:00:38,880
I saw his confidence and dedication.

1221
01:00:38,960 --> 01:00:41,760
But he might have tried a bit too hard.

1222
01:00:41,840 --> 01:00:46,400
I saw PP's effort,
but this isn't really his strong suit.

1223
01:00:46,480 --> 01:00:49,400
I'm not a good runway walker.

1224
01:00:49,480 --> 01:00:52,840
It makes me a bit insecure,
that I'm not that tall.

1225
01:00:52,920 --> 01:00:55,400
It makes me afraid to take long strides.

1226
01:00:55,480 --> 01:00:57,480
It makes my walk look awkward.

1227
01:00:59,040 --> 01:01:01,040
I don't know how others see me.

1228
01:01:01,120 --> 01:01:02,960
But I tried to walk naturally.

1229
01:01:11,920 --> 01:01:14,640
It's quite rock and roll.

1230
01:01:14,720 --> 01:01:16,680
It gives off a weird loincloth vibe.

1231
01:01:16,760 --> 01:01:18,440
Unfamiliar, but it was okay.

1232
01:01:18,520 --> 01:01:19,520
Rock on.

1233
01:01:21,800 --> 01:01:23,480
Donut, let me take a sniff.

1234
01:01:25,640 --> 01:01:27,120
Hey!

1235
01:01:29,160 --> 01:01:33,120
It looked cool and had a great vibe,
so it surprised us too.

1236
01:01:33,200 --> 01:01:35,520
That definitely wasn't in the rehearsal.

1237
01:01:35,600 --> 01:01:37,600
What's his name?

1238
01:01:37,680 --> 01:01:40,480
- His name is Donut.
- The noodle vendor?

1239
01:01:40,560 --> 01:01:41,560
Yes.

1240
01:01:41,640 --> 01:01:43,680
Donut really surprised me.

1241
01:01:43,760 --> 01:01:48,520
I see his improvement.
And today, I saw him take risks.

1242
01:01:48,600 --> 01:01:51,800
He tried to adapt and add his own flair.

1243
01:01:51,880 --> 01:01:55,800
It's not 100% yet, but he's getting there.

1244
01:02:00,240 --> 01:02:01,520
Took a whiff.

1245
01:02:01,600 --> 01:02:03,840
Didn't smell as good. Tossed it.

1246
01:02:03,920 --> 01:02:07,880
The flowers, the necklace… I tossed it.
I only want the AXE.

1247
01:02:07,960 --> 01:02:10,040
Fake flowers. They had no scent.

1248
01:02:10,120 --> 01:02:11,640
His energy was off.

1249
01:02:12,440 --> 01:02:14,760
Kimhan knew exactly what to do.
He brought it.

1250
01:02:14,840 --> 01:02:18,040
But honestly, it was a bit much.
The energy clashed.

1251
01:02:23,640 --> 01:02:25,200
I was so anxious for them.

1252
01:02:25,960 --> 01:02:28,160
Sweating for them. What was that?

1253
01:02:31,320 --> 01:02:33,120
There was a lot of improv.

1254
01:02:34,880 --> 01:02:38,200
The audience had to make eye contact
and smile at me.

1255
01:02:38,280 --> 01:02:41,160
"I smell great, want a whiff?"
That was my inner vibe.

1256
01:02:42,840 --> 01:02:45,880
With a setup like this,
you have to be confident.

1257
01:02:45,960 --> 01:02:47,120
PP's walk was solid.

1258
01:02:47,200 --> 01:02:50,480
I got my groove back and just went for it.

1259
01:02:57,840 --> 01:02:59,880
His hand drop had so much energy.

1260
01:02:59,960 --> 01:03:01,920
It was pretty sick. So cool.

1261
01:03:03,880 --> 01:03:04,960
Smelled amazing.

1262
01:03:09,560 --> 01:03:12,360
Mentor Pancake's team
was so boring to watch.

1263
01:03:12,440 --> 01:03:15,560
Mentor Pancake played it
a bit too safe. It was…

1264
01:03:15,640 --> 01:03:19,320
too repetitive,
which drained their energy.

1265
01:03:19,400 --> 01:03:22,920
It really lacked any element of surprise.

1266
01:03:23,000 --> 01:03:25,600
But they all looked confident.

1267
01:03:25,680 --> 01:03:28,000
Oh, dear.

1268
01:03:28,080 --> 01:03:30,040
Everyone, headbang right now!

1269
01:03:30,120 --> 01:03:34,840
I appreciate the effort,
but it needed more impact.

1270
01:03:34,920 --> 01:03:37,880
They should have been more playful.

1271
01:03:37,960 --> 01:03:40,280
I didn't want them to bomb out there.

1272
01:03:40,360 --> 01:03:43,080
Because I knew
they weren't sharp enough yet.

1273
01:03:45,200 --> 01:03:46,320
Where are you going?

1274
01:03:46,400 --> 01:03:48,840
When I turned around,
I couldn't reach her.

1275
01:03:48,920 --> 01:03:52,760
I couldn't grab her in time,
but it's okay. It might help my team.

1276
01:03:52,840 --> 01:03:54,160
Here comes Pancake.

1277
01:03:54,240 --> 01:03:55,800
What a surprise.

1278
01:04:04,080 --> 01:04:06,600
I turned around to see everyone cheering
for Mentor Pancake.

1279
01:04:14,680 --> 01:04:17,040
So gorgeous.
I was the only woman up there.

1280
01:04:17,880 --> 01:04:19,240
It's all Mentor Pancake.

1281
01:04:19,320 --> 01:04:20,720
Because she stood out.

1282
01:04:20,800 --> 01:04:22,240
Really?

1283
01:04:22,320 --> 01:04:25,560
Mentor Pancake naturally stands out,
so she stole the focus.

1284
01:04:25,640 --> 01:04:28,680
I didn't mean to overshadow the members.
We work as a team.

1285
01:04:28,760 --> 01:04:32,120
There were four great-smelling guys.
I had to join them.

1286
01:04:32,720 --> 01:04:36,920
I love how they told the story
through Mentor Pancake.

1287
01:04:37,000 --> 01:04:41,160
She just followed the scent of AXE.

1288
01:04:44,760 --> 01:04:48,760
Whose show is this? The members' or what?

1289
01:04:49,360 --> 01:04:50,760
Nice try, nice.

1290
01:04:50,840 --> 01:04:52,800
If only I could grab her in time.

1291
01:04:52,880 --> 01:04:54,440
I should have grabbed her.

1292
01:04:54,520 --> 01:04:56,520
I would like to praise our team today.

1293
01:04:56,600 --> 01:04:59,000
Everyone gave it their all.

1294
01:04:59,080 --> 01:05:01,640
They really tried hard and wanted to win.

1295
01:05:01,720 --> 01:05:05,240
What I really liked was the mood and tone.
It was very uplifting.

1296
01:05:05,320 --> 01:05:08,200
The finale was a surprise,
and Pancake nailed the brief.

1297
01:05:08,280 --> 01:05:09,800
I was shocked by some of it.

1298
01:05:09,880 --> 01:05:11,760
I didn't even know about some parts.

1299
01:05:11,840 --> 01:05:13,320
They designed this themselves.

1300
01:05:13,400 --> 01:05:17,680
Yes, I let them brainstorm
and design it in their own style.

1301
01:05:17,760 --> 01:05:20,680
I was stressed. The ending is crucial.

1302
01:05:20,760 --> 01:05:24,400
Start strong, finish strong.
Don't worry about the in-between.

1303
01:05:24,480 --> 01:05:26,720
Everyone did their absolute best.

1304
01:05:26,800 --> 01:05:29,680
Whether we nailed the brief,
that's up to the judges.

1305
01:05:35,680 --> 01:05:38,000
Please welcome the next team.
Team Mentor Off.

1306
01:05:40,880 --> 01:05:42,040
Let's go!

1307
01:05:44,520 --> 01:05:46,960
Bring us the energy! Bring us the energy!

1308
01:05:47,040 --> 01:05:48,040
Give me some energy!

1309
01:05:54,200 --> 01:05:55,800
This is my youngest child.

1310
01:05:55,880 --> 01:05:57,720
Mew walked in high heels.

1311
01:05:57,800 --> 01:05:59,880
Wow, amazing!

1312
01:05:59,960 --> 01:06:01,560
- Got to hand it to him.
- Me too.

1313
01:06:01,640 --> 01:06:03,240
He picked the hardest outfit.

1314
01:06:03,320 --> 01:06:06,240
I wanted to see his team
walk in heels too, to see if…

1315
01:06:06,320 --> 01:06:09,440
they were as fierce as he claimed
from the start.

1316
01:06:09,520 --> 01:06:12,640
- I'd be surprised if Bonus wore them.
- Let's see how they walk.

1317
01:06:12,720 --> 01:06:14,360
But I believe they can do it.

1318
01:06:14,440 --> 01:06:17,400
I'm confident
they'll fight for themselves.

1319
01:06:18,960 --> 01:06:20,920
Walk in and take my place.

1320
01:06:21,000 --> 01:06:22,360
Lights on. Cue the music.

1321
01:06:27,680 --> 01:06:30,520
I followed the brief.
Turned around and grabbed it.

1322
01:06:36,240 --> 01:06:37,080
Wake up!

1323
01:06:38,280 --> 01:06:42,640
We started from the back left cross
and walked up together.

1324
01:06:46,880 --> 01:06:49,400
We came up together,
but each with a different vibe.

1325
01:06:49,480 --> 01:06:51,760
We made good use of the X intersection.

1326
01:06:56,440 --> 01:06:57,360
Let's go.

1327
01:06:58,200 --> 01:07:00,640
- You don't need to speak anymore.
- Oh, sorry.

1328
01:07:02,600 --> 01:07:03,800
Nice.

1329
01:07:03,880 --> 01:07:07,080
- Look at those muscles.
- I'm half-naked a lot this season.

1330
01:07:08,080 --> 01:07:12,160
But that's okay. At least I got
to show off the body I've built all year.

1331
01:07:15,000 --> 01:07:16,840
The outfit? It is what it is.

1332
01:07:19,000 --> 01:07:20,240
But it's fabulous.

1333
01:07:20,320 --> 01:07:22,800
My team should've gotten
Team Off's outfits.

1334
01:07:22,880 --> 01:07:26,160
They walked out,
and it perfectly fit the venue.

1335
01:07:26,240 --> 01:07:28,400
What they did really well

1336
01:07:28,480 --> 01:07:32,640
was overcome their outfits and make it
look rock and roll. It fit the theme.

1337
01:07:32,720 --> 01:07:34,000
Bring it!

1338
01:07:35,560 --> 01:07:39,040
Mew is going strong today.
He looks so powerful in those heels.

1339
01:07:39,120 --> 01:07:40,520
What a surprise!

1340
01:07:40,600 --> 01:07:42,120
Look at Mew's attitude!

1341
01:07:42,200 --> 01:07:43,400
He's so confident.

1342
01:07:43,480 --> 01:07:45,040
I really have to hand it to him.

1343
01:07:45,120 --> 01:07:49,360
I don't know if everyone thought
it was fierce, but Mew was the fiercest.

1344
01:07:50,360 --> 01:07:52,920
Wow, that smells good. Smells so good.

1345
01:07:56,360 --> 01:07:59,080
Walking in heels hurts a bit.

1346
01:07:59,160 --> 01:08:00,760
But the show must go on.

1347
01:08:02,280 --> 01:08:05,760
I think it wowed them.
The audience seemed to love it.

1348
01:08:05,840 --> 01:08:09,960
Rome usually does better than this.
Maybe he wasn't confident?

1349
01:08:13,360 --> 01:08:16,560
I was overthinking my cues.
It was fine during rehearsal.

1350
01:08:16,640 --> 01:08:21,040
But on the actual runway, I focused
too much on cues and messed up.

1351
01:08:28,000 --> 01:08:29,760
These kids are really talented.

1352
01:08:29,840 --> 01:08:34,160
They're feeding off each other's energy.

1353
01:08:34,680 --> 01:08:36,359
That created so many great layers.

1354
01:08:40,240 --> 01:08:42,520
I yelled, "Woo!" and it was dead silent.

1355
01:08:46,640 --> 01:08:48,680
I stood there for a few seconds.

1356
01:08:48,760 --> 01:08:50,800
Then I had to say, "Make some noise!"

1357
01:08:50,880 --> 01:08:52,840
Make some noise!

1358
01:08:52,920 --> 01:08:54,680
Wow, he's so ripped.

1359
01:08:54,760 --> 01:08:57,040
He's definitely has that man-crush vibe.

1360
01:08:57,120 --> 01:08:59,560
Bonus isn't under any pressure.

1361
01:08:59,640 --> 01:09:01,920
He really embodies that show-off energy.

1362
01:09:06,720 --> 01:09:10,240
He's not here to play.

1363
01:09:13,640 --> 01:09:16,160
Mew today isn't the Mew
you're used to seeing.

1364
01:09:16,240 --> 01:09:18,520
Just keep walking with confidence.

1365
01:09:23,520 --> 01:09:26,359
In the grand finale,
everything turned out beautifully.

1366
01:09:26,439 --> 01:09:29,479
We wanted to showcase it perfectly
from a 360-degree view.

1367
01:09:31,319 --> 01:09:33,120
This team dances so well.

1368
01:09:33,200 --> 01:09:35,920
Their vibes perfectly blend together.

1369
01:09:36,000 --> 01:09:38,520
It's both a fashion show
and great entertainment.

1370
01:09:38,600 --> 01:09:39,600
The energy is great.

1371
01:09:40,479 --> 01:09:43,279
Walking back and forth is getting boring.

1372
01:09:44,920 --> 01:09:46,560
It's taking too long.

1373
01:09:46,640 --> 01:09:48,800
They're just repeating the same thing.

1374
01:09:48,880 --> 01:09:51,359
Repeating the same story
with the same guitar.

1375
01:09:51,439 --> 01:09:53,120
It's nothing special.

1376
01:09:54,120 --> 01:09:56,840
They need to rock the guitar.
Looks like a harp to me.

1377
01:09:56,920 --> 01:09:59,080
Does this fit the fashion show brief?

1378
01:09:59,160 --> 01:10:01,960
Look at this.

1379
01:10:02,040 --> 01:10:03,680
The blocking is a bit much.

1380
01:10:03,760 --> 01:10:06,560
Because we want to show
that we're a united team.

1381
01:10:07,080 --> 01:10:09,040
But cramming in this much…

1382
01:10:09,120 --> 01:10:11,000
Might make it look too crowded.

1383
01:10:11,080 --> 01:10:12,440
Keep it balanced, Off.

1384
01:10:16,360 --> 01:10:18,880
Having everyone join the finale…

1385
01:10:18,960 --> 01:10:21,240
That's enough to hype up the crowd.

1386
01:10:23,400 --> 01:10:25,840
Wow, end with a number seven pose.

1387
01:10:25,920 --> 01:10:27,680
It looks like a dash.

1388
01:10:27,760 --> 01:10:30,200
I must say, they have great teamwork.

1389
01:10:30,280 --> 01:10:31,360
I'm so happy.

1390
01:10:31,440 --> 01:10:33,440
Thanks to Off for the blocking.

1391
01:10:33,520 --> 01:10:36,240
He put thought into it.
Not everyone can pull this off.

1392
01:10:37,720 --> 01:10:39,040
So talented.

1393
01:10:39,120 --> 01:10:43,040
We gave it our all and hit the brief
perfectly. Number seven.

1394
01:10:43,120 --> 01:10:45,000
If this doesn't get us the win…

1395
01:10:45,080 --> 01:10:48,760
Then I really need to see what Pancake
and Mile's teams did.

1396
01:10:50,920 --> 01:10:53,960
Up next is the finale
from all three teams.

1397
01:11:09,000 --> 01:11:10,880
- Wow, Mew is unbelievable.
- Crazy bastard.

1398
01:11:15,200 --> 01:11:17,440
They can all walk.
No need to hype them up.

1399
01:11:18,480 --> 01:11:21,320
I have to give credit to Pancake
for the blocking.

1400
01:11:21,400 --> 01:11:23,120
It's actually really beautiful.

1401
01:11:34,480 --> 01:11:37,920
Give it up for our finale!

1402
01:11:40,800 --> 01:11:42,440
It's basic but perfect.

1403
01:11:42,520 --> 01:11:45,120
It's simple, relaxed, and clear.

1404
01:11:45,200 --> 01:11:49,880
A lot of new stars were born today.

1405
01:11:51,440 --> 01:11:53,600
Let's hear the feedback for each team.

1406
01:11:53,680 --> 01:11:56,120
Starting with Mentor Mile's team.

1407
01:11:56,200 --> 01:12:01,920
I was surprised.
You used the space so well.

1408
01:12:02,000 --> 01:12:05,000
The balance between everyone was great.

1409
01:12:05,080 --> 01:12:06,720
But someone stood out.

1410
01:12:06,800 --> 01:12:09,160
This guy was practically glowing.

1411
01:12:09,240 --> 01:12:10,200
Who is it?

1412
01:12:10,280 --> 01:12:11,880
I want to know too.

1413
01:12:11,960 --> 01:12:14,480
From the moment I saw his silhouette,

1414
01:12:14,560 --> 01:12:17,880
I knew he could make a career out of this.

1415
01:12:17,960 --> 01:12:19,200
It's Manyoo.

1416
01:12:19,280 --> 01:12:20,680
- Oh, Manyoo.
- Okay.

1417
01:12:20,760 --> 01:12:22,360
What I liked was

1418
01:12:22,440 --> 01:12:25,800
you balanced
between rock and roll and classy.

1419
01:12:25,880 --> 01:12:27,680
As for who stood out…

1420
01:12:27,760 --> 01:12:31,520
I agree about Manyoo. He was so natural.

1421
01:12:32,040 --> 01:12:35,080
Leo, overall, looked great.

1422
01:12:35,160 --> 01:12:36,880
He's definitely a crowd favorite.

1423
01:12:36,960 --> 01:12:39,240
The screams he got were insane.

1424
01:12:39,320 --> 01:12:41,640
Jacob looked a bit anxious.

1425
01:12:41,720 --> 01:12:43,840
Even though he looked great.

1426
01:12:43,920 --> 01:12:46,080
I think he was worried about his outfit.

1427
01:12:46,160 --> 01:12:50,920
I like to challenge timid people.
They need to survive the deep end.

1428
01:12:51,000 --> 01:12:56,000
To succeed, we need to push
past our limits.

1429
01:12:56,080 --> 01:12:57,520
Overall, it was good.

1430
01:12:57,600 --> 01:13:00,240
But you clearly separated the frontliners.

1431
01:13:00,320 --> 01:13:03,600
You need to figure out how to elevate
the people in the back.

1432
01:13:04,720 --> 01:13:08,120
We evaluated what went wrong.
We know our fate.

1433
01:13:08,200 --> 01:13:10,640
Next up, Pancake and Ananda's team.

1434
01:13:10,720 --> 01:13:13,440
I loved how you hyped up the crowd
at the end.

1435
01:13:13,520 --> 01:13:17,520
The finale really brought
the crowd to its peak.

1436
01:13:17,600 --> 01:13:21,240
But it would've been better
if you had that energy from the start.

1437
01:13:21,320 --> 01:13:24,360
One person really stood out.
Just from their silhouette…

1438
01:13:24,440 --> 01:13:26,720
- Great bone structure.
- You said that earlier.

1439
01:13:26,800 --> 01:13:29,200
- Just from his silhouette.
- Here.

1440
01:13:29,280 --> 01:13:32,120
A handsome man should have
a handsome shadow.

1441
01:13:32,200 --> 01:13:34,200
It's Donut.

1442
01:13:35,880 --> 01:13:38,480
I'm so glad. We know how hard he tried.

1443
01:13:38,560 --> 01:13:40,520
He's just so natural.

1444
01:13:40,600 --> 01:13:45,320
That makes it easy to mold him.

1445
01:13:45,400 --> 01:13:47,320
Are we talking about the same person?

1446
01:13:47,400 --> 01:13:49,600
Because Cindy wrote down here…

1447
01:13:49,680 --> 01:13:52,440
"Energy could be stronger.
He looked sleepy."

1448
01:13:52,520 --> 01:13:55,240
Paired with Kimhan,
they both looked sleepy.

1449
01:13:55,320 --> 01:13:56,520
It fell flat.

1450
01:13:56,600 --> 01:13:59,440
PP, I noticed he kept looking
at the others.

1451
01:13:59,520 --> 01:14:02,600
He lacked confidence in himself
and the blocking.

1452
01:14:02,680 --> 01:14:05,560
Another issue was Lincoln.

1453
01:14:05,640 --> 01:14:07,560
Since he's so handsome,

1454
01:14:07,640 --> 01:14:10,680
he tends to hold back and pose.

1455
01:14:10,760 --> 01:14:14,320
But in a fashion show,
attitude matters more than looks.

1456
01:14:14,400 --> 01:14:16,720
All right, that's two teams down.

1457
01:14:16,800 --> 01:14:19,120
Now, for our final team,
Mentor Off's team.

1458
01:14:19,760 --> 01:14:21,200
Hands are up.

1459
01:14:21,280 --> 01:14:23,200
I was worried about this team.

1460
01:14:23,280 --> 01:14:26,400
Given their outfits,
I wondered how it could be rock and roll.

1461
01:14:26,480 --> 01:14:30,680
But every single one of them showed
that fierce rock energy clearly.

1462
01:14:30,760 --> 01:14:34,120
And the constant surprises were great.

1463
01:14:34,200 --> 01:14:37,040
I can tell Off's team really gets along.

1464
01:14:37,120 --> 01:14:40,080
They have this unspoken synergy.

1465
01:14:40,160 --> 01:14:43,280
Their energy just flows effortlessly.

1466
01:14:43,360 --> 01:14:44,800
I hope you keep that up.

1467
01:14:44,880 --> 01:14:47,680
I'm glad they noticed that about our team.

1468
01:14:47,760 --> 01:14:51,480
Having a guy rocking high heels…

1469
01:14:51,560 --> 01:14:56,200
That made one person stand out
above the rest.

1470
01:14:56,280 --> 01:14:57,600
Who was it?

1471
01:14:57,680 --> 01:14:58,960
Who was it?

1472
01:14:59,040 --> 01:15:01,080
It was Bonus.

1473
01:15:01,160 --> 01:15:02,320
- Really?
- Yes.

1474
01:15:02,400 --> 01:15:07,240
Nowadays, we rarely see
such masculine men.

1475
01:15:07,320 --> 01:15:10,200
Mew was outstanding.
He gave off a team leader vibe.

1476
01:15:10,280 --> 01:15:12,160
It really seemed to suit him.

1477
01:15:12,240 --> 01:15:16,400
But the brief was cool and edgy.
He might have missed that a bit.

1478
01:15:16,480 --> 01:15:19,160
Rome looked very awkward.

1479
01:15:19,240 --> 01:15:21,440
Even though he has the best model look.

1480
01:15:21,520 --> 01:15:24,480
You led with Mew,
but Bonus stole the show.

1481
01:15:24,560 --> 01:15:26,520
A carefree person is dangerous.

1482
01:15:26,600 --> 01:15:28,120
He isn't worried.

1483
01:15:28,200 --> 01:15:31,440
This industry doesn't just need the best.
We need carefree ones.

1484
01:15:31,520 --> 01:15:33,200
Yes, thank you very much.

1485
01:15:33,280 --> 01:15:38,760
Before we announce the results,
let me announce the Popular Vote award.

1486
01:15:38,840 --> 01:15:42,360
The winner of the Popular Vote is…

1487
01:15:43,760 --> 01:15:45,520
- Mew.
- Oh, wow!

1488
01:15:46,200 --> 01:15:47,480
Thank you.

1489
01:15:47,560 --> 01:15:50,560
This means Mew gets a special privilege.

1490
01:15:50,640 --> 01:15:53,280
He won't be sent to the Black Room today.

1491
01:15:53,360 --> 01:15:56,040
Mew won the Popular Vote.

1492
01:15:56,120 --> 01:15:58,400
See? You can do it if you try.

1493
01:15:58,480 --> 01:16:02,520
And now, it's time for the final results.

1494
01:16:02,600 --> 01:16:06,720
Oab, the team that performed best
in today's campaign…

1495
01:16:06,800 --> 01:16:08,000
Which team is it?

1496
01:16:08,080 --> 01:16:13,560
The winner of The Iconic Dining
Presented by AXE is…

1497
01:16:18,400 --> 01:16:19,600
Mentor Off's team.

1498
01:16:22,120 --> 01:16:25,160
Congratulations to Mentor Off.

1499
01:16:25,240 --> 01:16:29,160
The winner of The Iconic Dining
Presented by AXE.

1500
01:16:29,240 --> 01:16:32,080
- Such a hard sell.
- I'm happy now.

1501
01:16:32,160 --> 01:16:33,880
This is what happens when you fight.

1502
01:16:33,960 --> 01:16:36,560
We won with two mentors.
We'd win even with just one.

1503
01:16:36,640 --> 01:16:39,680
I like him being cocky. I love it.

1504
01:16:39,760 --> 01:16:42,800
I'm not just all talk, Mile.
The results speak for themselves.

1505
01:16:42,880 --> 01:16:45,520
But today's surprises aren't over yet.

1506
01:16:45,600 --> 01:16:49,120
Because today, we have a special prize
for one person.

1507
01:16:49,200 --> 01:16:50,960
The one who performed the best.

1508
01:16:51,040 --> 01:16:53,360
The winner gets a special prize from AXE.

1509
01:16:53,440 --> 01:16:57,880
A one-year supply
of confidence-boosting products.

1510
01:16:57,960 --> 01:17:00,400
Along with 30,000 baht.

1511
01:17:00,480 --> 01:17:03,800
Oab, the contestant who stood out the most

1512
01:17:03,880 --> 01:17:07,160
and led their team to victory today is…

1513
01:17:07,240 --> 01:17:09,400
The one suited to be our AXE Guy is…

1514
01:17:11,080 --> 01:17:13,000
Bonus.

1515
01:17:13,640 --> 01:17:16,000
- Unbelievable.
- Look at Ma's face. Look at her.

1516
01:17:16,080 --> 01:17:19,080
There's practically a pop-up here saying,
"I told you so."

1517
01:17:19,160 --> 01:17:21,560
We swept all three awards today.

1518
01:17:21,640 --> 01:17:24,520
Ultimately, credit goes to the guys.
We just guided them.

1519
01:17:25,760 --> 01:17:27,560
I'm using my Master Mentor privilege.

1520
01:17:29,040 --> 01:17:30,120
I'm changing the rules.

1521
01:17:30,200 --> 01:17:32,480
Here we go. What now?

1522
01:17:32,560 --> 01:17:34,080
That's intense.

1523
01:17:34,160 --> 01:17:36,160
The Master Mentor is ruthless.

1524
01:17:36,240 --> 01:17:38,280
Changing the winner?

1525
01:17:38,360 --> 01:17:40,080
- No, Mew still wins.
- I see!

1526
01:17:40,160 --> 01:17:45,320
Mew can pass this privilege to anyone.

1527
01:17:45,400 --> 01:17:47,600
It's entirely up to Mew.

1528
01:17:47,680 --> 01:17:49,440
Or he can forfeit it.

1529
01:17:49,520 --> 01:17:50,840
It's up to him.

1530
01:17:50,920 --> 01:17:52,400
An even bigger surprise.

1531
01:17:52,480 --> 01:17:54,960
The Popular Vote winner
is already on the winning team.

1532
01:17:55,040 --> 01:17:58,000
Giving Mew full control to pass it on.

1533
01:17:58,080 --> 01:18:01,400
Giving a rival immunity would be fun.

1534
01:18:01,480 --> 01:18:03,560
Don't forget, Mew didn't watch the show.

1535
01:18:03,640 --> 01:18:05,760
How can he judge who was good or bad?

1536
01:18:05,840 --> 01:18:07,960
I think we have a good relationship.

1537
01:18:08,040 --> 01:18:09,400
Oh, you want that perk.

1538
01:18:09,480 --> 01:18:11,600
Don't mess with me. I'll handle this.

1539
01:18:11,680 --> 01:18:14,800
Today, we would like
to thank all our judges.

1540
01:18:14,880 --> 01:18:17,280
For judging our campaign today.

1541
01:18:17,360 --> 01:18:19,920
And of course,
thank you to our three mentors.

1542
01:18:24,280 --> 01:18:26,840
So this is what the smell
of a winner is like?

1543
01:18:26,920 --> 01:18:30,480
Guess who goes if you send
your weakest and strongest.

1544
01:18:30,560 --> 01:18:32,760
Who gets cut first if Off is the judge?

1545
01:18:32,840 --> 01:18:35,520
Careful. If we're playing a game,
I won't hold back.

1546
01:18:35,600 --> 01:18:38,680
What's one plus one?
Do I need to do the math for you?

1547
01:18:38,760 --> 01:18:43,120
I'm not scared. Bring it on. I'm ready.

1548
01:18:43,200 --> 01:18:46,880
No hard feelings. Anything can happen
on <i>The Face</i>, right?

1549
01:19:17,240 --> 01:19:18,280
Is it him?

1550
01:19:18,360 --> 01:19:20,640
- Hello.
- Hello, guys.

1551
01:19:20,720 --> 01:19:23,400
I was shocked. Why did he talk like this?

1552
01:19:23,480 --> 01:19:26,520
Usually, it means
we messed up if he's nice.

1553
01:19:26,600 --> 01:19:28,600
Let's talk about the performance first.

1554
01:19:28,680 --> 01:19:34,840
Suppose I asked who was
a bit weaker than the rest.

1555
01:19:35,840 --> 01:19:36,760
You know it, right?

1556
01:19:36,840 --> 01:19:39,120
You couldn't remember the blocking.

1557
01:19:39,200 --> 01:19:41,120
Rome, you had a slight hesitation.

1558
01:19:41,880 --> 01:19:43,640
- Spaced out.
- You spaced out once.

1559
01:19:43,720 --> 01:19:44,840
Yes, I remember.

1560
01:19:44,920 --> 01:19:48,640
I was so stressed.
I mentally prepared myself.

1561
01:19:48,720 --> 01:19:50,440
Just in case it was me.

1562
01:19:50,520 --> 01:19:53,520
- Pom, you screamed a bit too much.
- Really?

1563
01:19:54,920 --> 01:19:58,080
But was it good? It fit the vibe.

1564
01:19:58,160 --> 01:19:59,360
Were you nervous then?

1565
01:19:59,440 --> 01:20:01,120
- No.
- You were relaxed?

1566
01:20:01,200 --> 01:20:04,880
It's all or nothing.
I have no middle ground.

1567
01:20:04,960 --> 01:20:08,400
If I had to send someone to the Black Room
today, it would be you.

1568
01:20:08,480 --> 01:20:11,880
Were you the weakest link in there?

1569
01:20:11,960 --> 01:20:13,480
I guess so.

1570
01:20:13,560 --> 01:20:15,280
But you won the popular vote.

1571
01:20:16,960 --> 01:20:19,760
Others saw that you gave it your all.

1572
01:20:19,840 --> 01:20:23,840
Today, I have wings on me. I flew down
from heaven just to take the crown.

1573
01:20:23,920 --> 01:20:26,880
You saved yourself,
but you can't save your friend.

1574
01:20:26,960 --> 01:20:29,800
So you have to make the choice,
because I don't want to.

1575
01:20:29,880 --> 01:20:31,200
I can't choose.

1576
01:20:31,280 --> 01:20:33,680
You have to. If you don't, I'm dead.

1577
01:20:33,760 --> 01:20:35,200
I can't choose.

1578
01:20:35,280 --> 01:20:38,400
It's stressful. I don't want
to send anyone to the Black Room.

1579
01:20:39,000 --> 01:20:40,640
I think everyone did great.

1580
01:20:40,720 --> 01:20:42,720
So I let the mentor choose.

1581
01:20:43,720 --> 01:20:44,560
Okay.

1582
01:20:45,400 --> 01:20:47,160
I won't pick anyone, because we won.

1583
01:20:49,920 --> 01:20:50,960
Let's go!

1584
01:20:52,240 --> 01:20:53,080
We did it!

1585
01:20:53,160 --> 01:20:55,200
Great job, guys!

1586
01:20:55,280 --> 01:20:58,680
Team Mentor Off won the campaign again.

1587
01:20:58,760 --> 01:21:00,880
No one has to go to the Black Room.

1588
01:21:08,080 --> 01:21:10,280
- Hello.
- Hello.

1589
01:21:11,040 --> 01:21:12,400
Yes.

1590
01:21:17,560 --> 01:21:19,440
Come on, don't be so tense.

1591
01:21:19,520 --> 01:21:22,640
- Loosen up. Are you tense?
- Just anxious. Not tense.

1592
01:21:22,720 --> 01:21:24,720
How do you think we did that day?

1593
01:21:24,800 --> 01:21:27,040
I think everyone did their best.

1594
01:21:27,120 --> 01:21:28,680
- Yes, exactly.
- Talk it out.

1595
01:21:28,760 --> 01:21:31,160
But everyone worked very hard.

1596
01:21:31,240 --> 01:21:33,600
Ananda and I are proud of you for that.

1597
01:21:33,680 --> 01:21:37,200
I had a feeling
when she started with compliments.

1598
01:21:37,800 --> 01:21:39,120
And then came the "but."

1599
01:21:40,400 --> 01:21:43,480
So I could guess what was coming.

1600
01:21:43,560 --> 01:21:45,960
I saw it during rehearsal.

1601
01:21:46,040 --> 01:21:51,000
Everyone was trying so hard
to help create things.

1602
01:21:51,080 --> 01:21:53,440
There's no right or wrong.

1603
01:21:53,520 --> 01:21:56,440
It's just whether they liked it or not.

1604
01:21:56,520 --> 01:21:59,280
How much they liked it. That's all.

1605
01:21:59,360 --> 01:22:02,840
We can always adapt and keep improving.

1606
01:22:02,920 --> 01:22:03,920
Right?

1607
01:22:04,000 --> 01:22:05,120
And the result is…

1608
01:22:06,040 --> 01:22:07,120
we lost.

1609
01:22:09,400 --> 01:22:10,880
My heart sank.

1610
01:22:10,960 --> 01:22:14,120
She complimented everyone.

1611
01:22:14,200 --> 01:22:16,440
But in the end, she told us we lost.

1612
01:22:18,800 --> 01:22:21,160
- Hi, Mile.
- How's it going?

1613
01:22:21,240 --> 01:22:23,000
- Hello.
- Hello.

1614
01:22:23,080 --> 01:22:25,880
I'm not sure if they were relaxed
because they were confident

1615
01:22:25,960 --> 01:22:28,400
or if they were trying to be brave.

1616
01:22:28,480 --> 01:22:31,960
To keep the mood light
before sending someone to the Black Room.

1617
01:22:32,040 --> 01:22:33,520
Can I have the stone, please?

1618
01:22:33,600 --> 01:22:36,080
Our creative team
really believes in stones.

1619
01:22:36,160 --> 01:22:40,920
So I thought, "Why not give it a try?"
I have one for each of you.

1620
01:22:41,000 --> 01:22:42,920
- Thank you.
- One for each of you.

1621
01:22:43,000 --> 01:22:44,400
Pick one.

1622
01:22:44,480 --> 01:22:46,560
We are Team Milestone.

1623
01:22:46,640 --> 01:22:48,440
Thank you so much, Mile.

1624
01:22:48,520 --> 01:22:51,520
Team Milestone. We've got stones today.

1625
01:22:51,600 --> 01:22:55,160
Everyone looks like…
What do you call them? Power Rangers.

1626
01:22:55,240 --> 01:22:57,280
Everyone gets their own color.

1627
01:22:57,360 --> 01:23:00,800
I brought these to show you that

1628
01:23:00,880 --> 01:23:03,760
stones just exist,
and they have different shapes, right?

1629
01:23:03,840 --> 01:23:07,240
When a stone is in the wrong place,
it's totally worthless.

1630
01:23:07,880 --> 01:23:11,800
But if it's in the right place,
its value can be incredibly high.

1631
01:23:11,880 --> 01:23:15,880
But value depends
on who's measuring it, right?

1632
01:23:15,960 --> 01:23:18,600
Whereas your true worth
is something you define.

1633
01:23:18,680 --> 01:23:22,720
A stone in the right place
is a good stone. It has value.

1634
01:23:22,800 --> 01:23:24,880
And others can easily see its worth.

1635
01:23:25,480 --> 01:23:27,280
But today isn't that day.

1636
01:23:31,400 --> 01:23:33,400
When will we ever beat them?

1637
01:23:33,480 --> 01:23:38,440
My heart sank a bit too,
because I know everyone did great.

1638
01:23:38,520 --> 01:23:39,920
Everyone tried their best.

1639
01:23:40,000 --> 01:23:43,360
If there's one person today
that Ananda and I discussed…

1640
01:23:43,440 --> 01:23:46,960
based on your performances…

1641
01:23:50,240 --> 01:23:53,360
- I know you worked very hard, PP.
- Yes.

1642
01:23:53,440 --> 01:23:54,920
But you have more room to grow.

1643
01:23:55,000 --> 01:23:58,080
Pancake chose PP for the Black Room.

1644
01:23:58,840 --> 01:24:00,520
He's like a little brother to me.

1645
01:24:00,600 --> 01:24:02,640
I don't know what Off is planning today.

1646
01:24:02,720 --> 01:24:05,320
We don't know what he'll do.

1647
01:24:05,400 --> 01:24:07,360
But he wants a fighter.

1648
01:24:07,440 --> 01:24:09,880
Even if he decides
to eliminate both of you today,

1649
01:24:09,960 --> 01:24:12,440
if you fight,
you leave with your head held high.

1650
01:24:12,520 --> 01:24:14,080
Any final words? Let's go over it.

1651
01:24:14,160 --> 01:24:15,960
What's wrong? Can you read his mind?

1652
01:24:17,440 --> 01:24:19,040
Look at Donut's face.

1653
01:24:19,680 --> 01:24:22,040
- Don't cry. You'll make me cry.
- I'm just sad.

1654
01:24:22,120 --> 01:24:26,120
We spend so much time training together.
We're so close.

1655
01:24:26,200 --> 01:24:28,320
He's like a little brother to me.

1656
01:24:28,400 --> 01:24:30,800
- But we're still here.
- I know.

1657
01:24:30,880 --> 01:24:33,760
- Donut, we're not going anywhere.
- Right.

1658
01:24:33,840 --> 01:24:35,520
I'm just worried about him.

1659
01:24:36,560 --> 01:24:38,560
Why did we have to lose again? Why?

1660
01:24:38,640 --> 01:24:40,320
If I win next time, I'll…

1661
01:24:44,960 --> 01:24:47,840
This Black Room was a tough decision.

1662
01:24:47,920 --> 01:24:52,360
I think this person will gain
a lot of experience

1663
01:24:52,440 --> 01:24:54,920
if they enter the Black Room.

1664
01:24:55,000 --> 01:24:59,040
I believe
it was a very tough decision for Mile.

1665
01:24:59,120 --> 01:25:01,320
Okay, I'm sending Jacob today.

1666
01:25:01,400 --> 01:25:02,800
- Okay.
- All right.

1667
01:25:02,880 --> 01:25:04,480
It's already episode four.

1668
01:25:04,560 --> 01:25:05,880
We're all very close.

1669
01:25:05,960 --> 01:25:09,120
There were five judges this round.

1670
01:25:09,200 --> 01:25:13,000
They all said you were…

1671
01:25:13,080 --> 01:25:16,480
- the weakest link in the finale.
- Right, understood.

1672
01:25:16,560 --> 01:25:18,560
It hurt me because that's what I heard.

1673
01:25:18,640 --> 01:25:22,520
I believe that if you talk to Off
and fight for it,

1674
01:25:22,600 --> 01:25:25,120
he might reconsider.

1675
01:25:25,200 --> 01:25:29,240
- And I hope you come back.
- I hope so too.

1676
01:25:29,320 --> 01:25:32,080
Why does today feel just like
the last time Ananda won?

1677
01:25:32,160 --> 01:25:34,760
It felt somewhat relaxed.

1678
01:25:34,840 --> 01:25:38,120
But not that much.
When the time came, it was stressful.

1679
01:25:38,200 --> 01:25:40,760
Two people could go home this round.
I felt like…

1680
01:25:40,840 --> 01:25:44,360
"Oh, no. There's a high chance
he won't come back."

1681
01:25:48,960 --> 01:25:50,640
There's also the Axe Guy award.

1682
01:25:50,720 --> 01:25:54,920
For the person who secured
our victory today.

1683
01:25:55,000 --> 01:25:56,560
- You.
- Hey.

1684
01:25:56,640 --> 01:25:57,840
Bo?

1685
01:25:57,920 --> 01:25:59,880
- Yes.
- With the guitar?

1686
01:25:59,960 --> 01:26:01,600
Oh, man, I was so smooth.

1687
01:26:01,680 --> 01:26:04,440
Besides that, you get 30,000 baht.

1688
01:26:04,520 --> 01:26:07,520
And a free year's supply of Axe.

1689
01:26:07,600 --> 01:26:08,440
- What?
- Oh, wow.

1690
01:26:09,080 --> 01:26:10,240
I prayed this morning.

1691
01:26:10,320 --> 01:26:12,000
- You're rich now.
- Are you serious?

1692
01:26:12,080 --> 01:26:15,320
I was so happy. My prayers worked!

1693
01:26:18,880 --> 01:26:21,360
Let's stress over who to eliminate today.

1694
01:26:22,880 --> 01:26:24,480
- Let's do this.
- Seriously?

1695
01:26:24,560 --> 01:26:26,800
We have a special privilege.

1696
01:26:26,880 --> 01:26:28,800
You have the right to save someone.

1697
01:26:28,880 --> 01:26:31,800
You can save someone
from Pancake or Mile's team.

1698
01:26:31,880 --> 01:26:33,680
Anyone at all.

1699
01:26:33,760 --> 01:26:35,720
Or we don't have to use it at all.

1700
01:26:36,440 --> 01:26:40,960
Everyone has tried their best. If we must
save someone, I want the mentor to choose.

1701
01:26:41,040 --> 01:26:45,040
Between the two members
sent to the Dark Room.

1702
01:26:45,120 --> 01:26:47,000
Then just send us good contestants.

1703
01:26:47,080 --> 01:26:49,800
Send whoever you think belongs
in the Black Room.

1704
01:27:16,040 --> 01:27:17,080
Hello.

1705
01:27:17,160 --> 01:27:18,280
I was shocked.

1706
01:27:18,360 --> 01:27:22,880
When PP and Jacob showed up,
I wasn't expecting them.

1707
01:27:22,960 --> 01:27:27,880
I want to know why
your mentors sent you here.

1708
01:27:27,960 --> 01:27:29,520
- Jacob?
- Yes?

1709
01:27:29,600 --> 01:27:31,360
I walked well during the team walk.

1710
01:27:31,440 --> 01:27:35,200
But during the finale,
I might have looked a bit worried.

1711
01:27:35,280 --> 01:27:36,880
What were you so worried about?

1712
01:27:36,960 --> 01:27:38,520
It really showed in your eyes.

1713
01:27:38,600 --> 01:27:40,880
It was my outfit. It was very long.

1714
01:27:40,960 --> 01:27:43,800
During the final walk, I kept thinking…

1715
01:27:43,880 --> 01:27:47,040
- "What if I knock over all the glasses?"
- Right. I see.

1716
01:27:47,120 --> 01:27:48,760
It probably showed on my face…

1717
01:27:48,840 --> 01:27:51,400
- It definitely did.
- Really? I was overthinking it.

1718
01:27:51,480 --> 01:27:53,960
Yes, honestly, it was just the outfit.

1719
01:27:55,560 --> 01:27:56,440
Go on.

1720
01:27:56,520 --> 01:28:00,360
From the start,
I've never been great at the runway.

1721
01:28:00,440 --> 01:28:03,480
But the latest campaign was a team effort.

1722
01:28:03,560 --> 01:28:05,840
So I didn't think I was the worst.

1723
01:28:05,920 --> 01:28:10,720
But I guess I didn't deliver
what the client wanted.

1724
01:28:10,800 --> 01:28:13,440
So it wasn't good enough.

1725
01:28:13,520 --> 01:28:15,400
From what I heard from the judges,

1726
01:28:15,480 --> 01:28:19,520
Lincoln was the weakest link.

1727
01:28:19,600 --> 01:28:22,040
So why did they send PP?

1728
01:28:22,120 --> 01:28:25,000
They might be looking at the big picture.

1729
01:28:25,080 --> 01:28:30,360
He might have potential
in the next campaign or master class.

1730
01:28:30,440 --> 01:28:32,760
- Oh, really?
- But honestly, I feel like

1731
01:28:32,840 --> 01:28:35,840
there isn't much difference between us.

1732
01:28:35,920 --> 01:28:37,080
I feel the same way.

1733
01:28:37,760 --> 01:28:38,920
That's surprising too.

1734
01:28:39,000 --> 01:28:41,840
It shouldn't be Jacob.
It should be someone else, right?

1735
01:28:41,920 --> 01:28:43,560
I didn't think it would be Jacob.

1736
01:28:43,640 --> 01:28:45,320
I thought it would be Gluf.

1737
01:28:45,400 --> 01:28:47,320
Because Gluf missed the last challenge.

1738
01:28:47,400 --> 01:28:48,920
If he missed a challenge,

1739
01:28:49,000 --> 01:28:52,440
he shouldn't get to compete
in the following ones.

1740
01:28:52,520 --> 01:28:55,400
Do you think you're the weakest?
Is that why you're here?

1741
01:28:55,480 --> 01:28:58,400
I don't feel like I'm the weakest link.

1742
01:28:58,480 --> 01:29:02,400
I don't think anyone on my team is weak.
We all have different characters.

1743
01:29:03,000 --> 01:29:06,280
Right now, I have
an immunity pass from Mew.

1744
01:29:06,360 --> 01:29:10,920
I can save someone from the Black Room.
But his team shouldn't have won.

1745
01:29:11,000 --> 01:29:12,800
So the Master Mentor said

1746
01:29:12,880 --> 01:29:16,480
Mew could use it to save anyone.

1747
01:29:16,560 --> 01:29:20,200
Mew couldn't choose.
So he gave the power to me.

1748
01:29:20,920 --> 01:29:22,240
He let me decide.

1749
01:29:22,320 --> 01:29:25,840
I'm going to go fight with everyone
to keep both of you.

1750
01:29:26,640 --> 01:29:28,440
It's not a game.

1751
01:29:28,520 --> 01:29:31,480
I'm going to ask them
if they've thought this through.

1752
01:29:31,560 --> 01:29:33,960
"You sent him here.
Are you sure about this?"

1753
01:29:34,040 --> 01:29:35,200
It's up to them.

1754
01:29:36,080 --> 01:29:37,320
Wait here.

1755
01:29:41,280 --> 01:29:42,840
I haven't made a decision yet.

1756
01:29:42,920 --> 01:29:44,720
The power is in my hands now.

1757
01:29:44,800 --> 01:29:47,880
Because Mew won the popular vote.

1758
01:29:47,960 --> 01:29:52,160
He can save one person
from going into the Black Room.

1759
01:29:52,240 --> 01:29:55,600
So the two people
in the Black Room right now…

1760
01:29:55,680 --> 01:29:57,880
I don't think they belong there.

1761
01:29:57,960 --> 01:30:00,320
He just wants to mess with everyone.

1762
01:30:00,400 --> 01:30:01,680
It's so obvious.

1763
01:30:01,760 --> 01:30:06,480
Mentor Pan, the one who got criticized
the most wasn't PP, right?

1764
01:30:06,560 --> 01:30:08,760
Lincoln got the most criticism.

1765
01:30:08,840 --> 01:30:12,360
The one who should be
in the Black Room is Lincoln.

1766
01:30:12,440 --> 01:30:14,680
Is he the favorite? I don't get it.

1767
01:30:14,760 --> 01:30:17,080
PP said he's not the weakest.

1768
01:30:17,160 --> 01:30:18,320
Did PP say that?

1769
01:30:18,400 --> 01:30:19,720
It's true.

1770
01:30:19,800 --> 01:30:22,040
- Did PP say that?
- It's true, Mentor Pan.

1771
01:30:23,480 --> 01:30:25,720
It contradicts reality.

1772
01:30:25,800 --> 01:30:27,920
What is Mentor Off talking about?

1773
01:30:28,000 --> 01:30:29,600
I don't want to change.

1774
01:30:29,680 --> 01:30:30,600
You won't change?

1775
01:30:30,680 --> 01:30:31,920
What right do you have?

1776
01:30:32,000 --> 01:30:34,160
Actually, isn't it Mew's?

1777
01:30:34,240 --> 01:30:36,880
- Mew, please explain.
- Why burden the mentor, Mew?

1778
01:30:36,960 --> 01:30:38,120
Why play the angel?

1779
01:30:40,320 --> 01:30:44,920
I gave my right to Mentor Off
because he can decide better.

1780
01:30:45,000 --> 01:30:46,400
Because he's a mentor.

1781
01:30:46,480 --> 01:30:49,960
I saw everyone doing well.
I don't want to save just one person.

1782
01:30:50,040 --> 01:30:52,040
If you do, others might suffer.

1783
01:30:52,120 --> 01:30:53,960
- You can choose not to.
- If you don't…

1784
01:30:54,040 --> 01:30:55,600
The mentor can eliminate both.

1785
01:30:55,680 --> 01:30:57,920
Of course. I would eliminate both.

1786
01:30:58,000 --> 01:31:00,600
But I agree with Mentor Off
to eliminate both.

1787
01:31:01,960 --> 01:31:05,320
He wears angel wings,
but he's a wizard too.

1788
01:31:05,400 --> 01:31:07,480
I should've broken those wings earlier.

1789
01:31:07,560 --> 01:31:08,960
Mile.

1790
01:31:09,040 --> 01:31:12,720
As for Mile, I think here…

1791
01:31:12,800 --> 01:31:13,760
- Gluf.
- Yes.

1792
01:31:13,840 --> 01:31:15,960
He missed a challenge twice.

1793
01:31:16,040 --> 01:31:18,800
Why does he have the right
to take part in the third one?

1794
01:31:18,880 --> 01:31:22,240
The director said it's fine
to miss the second one.

1795
01:31:22,320 --> 01:31:23,160
Really?

1796
01:31:23,240 --> 01:31:25,200
I was shocked the show let him skip it.

1797
01:31:25,280 --> 01:31:27,640
- Oh, a favorite. He has connections.
- No.

1798
01:31:27,720 --> 01:31:29,800
He had chickenpox back then, right?

1799
01:31:29,880 --> 01:31:31,160
Do you want to catch it?

1800
01:31:31,240 --> 01:31:33,880
I'm still confused. The thing with Gluf…

1801
01:31:33,960 --> 01:31:35,520
It has been two or three weeks.

1802
01:31:35,600 --> 01:31:38,280
Why keep dragging it out? What is this?

1803
01:31:38,360 --> 01:31:41,440
Doesn't that mean
he shouldn't be in the Final Walk?

1804
01:31:41,520 --> 01:31:43,360
Because he missed a challenge.

1805
01:31:43,440 --> 01:31:46,480
Let's ask the kid. Let's hear from Gluf.

1806
01:31:46,560 --> 01:31:47,440
Speak up, Gluf.

1807
01:31:47,520 --> 01:31:51,240
I've always said
I didn't choose to get chickenpox.

1808
01:31:51,320 --> 01:31:53,520
I wanted to compete like everyone else.

1809
01:31:53,600 --> 01:31:56,000
But I couldn't make it,
so I'm making up for it now.

1810
01:31:56,080 --> 01:31:59,760
I missed challenges and exams
while filming this show.

1811
01:31:59,840 --> 01:32:01,160
I could re-take exams.

1812
01:32:01,240 --> 01:32:04,120
But Mile, if you had never sent Gluf in,

1813
01:32:04,200 --> 01:32:06,680
would the producers
have allowed him to continue?

1814
01:32:06,760 --> 01:32:09,520
I understand if Gluf hates me.
It's not surprising.

1815
01:32:09,600 --> 01:32:11,640
But I have to do this
to make things clear.

1816
01:32:11,720 --> 01:32:14,280
Should Mile have explained it to Gluf
from the start?

1817
01:32:14,360 --> 01:32:15,800
Why, Mile?

1818
01:32:15,880 --> 01:32:17,240
You're afraid he'll hate you?

1819
01:32:17,320 --> 01:32:19,120
- What should we do?
- With what?

1820
01:32:19,200 --> 01:32:22,080
Does Gluf have the right
to participate in the Final Walk?

1821
01:32:22,160 --> 01:32:23,800
Since he missed a challenge.

1822
01:32:23,880 --> 01:32:25,720
The day Gluf didn't show up,

1823
01:32:25,800 --> 01:32:29,040
the show let him rest for safety reasons.

1824
01:32:29,120 --> 01:32:33,120
But we gave the mentors the right

1825
01:32:33,200 --> 01:32:38,400
to keep Gluf in the following episodes.

1826
01:32:38,480 --> 01:32:41,000
But when it comes to the Final Walk,

1827
01:32:41,080 --> 01:32:45,720
Gluf has no right to participate.

1828
01:32:45,800 --> 01:32:47,760
You can't miss a challenge.

1829
01:32:47,840 --> 01:32:50,000
Why cut off his chances so easily?

1830
01:32:50,640 --> 01:32:52,360
I feel bad for him.

1831
01:32:52,440 --> 01:32:55,560
Because the people in the Final Walk

1832
01:32:55,640 --> 01:32:58,080
must have participated in every episode.

1833
01:32:58,160 --> 01:32:59,000
I agree.

1834
01:32:59,080 --> 01:33:02,880
The Final Walk participants
should pass everything.

1835
01:33:02,960 --> 01:33:04,600
They should be in every campaign.

1836
01:33:04,680 --> 01:33:07,080
After this,
Gluf has the right to everything.

1837
01:33:07,160 --> 01:33:08,760
But not the Final Walk.

1838
01:33:08,840 --> 01:33:09,680
Then why stay?

1839
01:33:09,760 --> 01:33:12,440
Eliminate him.
He doesn't have the same rights.

1840
01:33:12,520 --> 01:33:15,400
Even knowing
we won't reach the Final Walk,

1841
01:33:15,480 --> 01:33:17,760
the journey itself is valuable.

1842
01:33:17,840 --> 01:33:18,760
Is that okay?

1843
01:33:18,840 --> 01:33:19,880
It's okay.

1844
01:33:19,960 --> 01:33:21,280
That's it.

1845
01:33:22,360 --> 01:33:24,680
Oh, wow.

1846
01:33:24,760 --> 01:33:25,960
Dropping a bomb like that.

1847
01:33:26,880 --> 01:33:28,080
I'm shocked too.

1848
01:33:28,160 --> 01:33:30,640
I just fought for you guys.

1849
01:33:30,720 --> 01:33:32,400
But they refused to change.

1850
01:33:32,480 --> 01:33:35,640
I went out to fight for PP
and fought for Jacob.

1851
01:33:35,720 --> 01:33:36,920
It's not even my job.

1852
01:33:40,720 --> 01:33:42,360
So I have to make a decision now.

1853
01:33:42,440 --> 01:33:46,280
Because even if I save you,
they'll just eliminate my team anyway.

1854
01:33:52,280 --> 01:33:54,480
- Sorry.
- It's okay.

1855
01:33:54,560 --> 01:33:56,440
You might not be The Face yet.

1856
01:33:58,760 --> 01:34:00,360
You might not be The Face yet.

1857
01:34:00,440 --> 01:34:01,600
Right.

1858
01:34:01,680 --> 01:34:04,000
- I fought for you. I really tried.
- I know.

1859
01:34:04,080 --> 01:34:05,280
Yes.

1860
01:34:05,360 --> 01:34:08,240
I understand Mile.
But I wanted to keep going.

1861
01:34:08,320 --> 01:34:10,320
And I think I'm the weakest on the team.

1862
01:34:10,400 --> 01:34:13,320
Honestly, I think
I have the least experience.

1863
01:34:13,400 --> 01:34:15,320
I just really wanted our team to win.

1864
01:34:15,400 --> 01:34:17,880
And I believe in everyone's abilities.

1865
01:34:18,880 --> 01:34:20,560
Off tried his best for us.

1866
01:34:20,640 --> 01:34:22,280
Both me and Jacob.

1867
01:34:22,360 --> 01:34:24,600
Since he couldn't save both of us,

1868
01:34:24,680 --> 01:34:26,760
eliminating us both might be
the better choice.

1869
01:34:26,840 --> 01:34:31,360
I'm sad, but my dream doesn't stop here.

1870
01:34:31,440 --> 01:34:32,760
I'll keep going.

1871
01:34:36,160 --> 01:34:37,560
You came alone?

1872
01:34:37,640 --> 01:34:38,720
Yes.

1873
01:34:38,800 --> 01:34:40,760
Since Mile won't swap anyone out,

1874
01:34:40,840 --> 01:34:43,720
I won't be using

1875
01:34:43,800 --> 01:34:45,480
the power Mew gave me.

1876
01:34:46,640 --> 01:34:49,560
It's a huge shame Jacob didn't return.

1877
01:34:51,120 --> 01:34:53,160
- He asked me to give this.
- Like a movie.

1878
01:34:53,240 --> 01:34:56,040
Oh, my god. This scene is so touching.

1879
01:34:56,120 --> 01:34:57,680
I understand your decision,

1880
01:34:57,760 --> 01:34:59,360
but this stone is burning hot.

1881
01:34:59,440 --> 01:35:01,400
- He must've been stressed.
- He sure was.

1882
01:35:01,480 --> 01:35:02,360
It's really hot.

1883
01:35:02,440 --> 01:35:04,240
The stone Jacob held.

1884
01:35:04,320 --> 01:35:07,120
So what? Mile, does knowing save him?

1885
01:35:07,200 --> 01:35:08,320
It does not.

1886
01:35:08,400 --> 01:35:09,720
I saw Cob holding it.

1887
01:35:09,800 --> 01:35:11,640
Maybe he was going to throw it at me.

1888
01:35:11,720 --> 01:35:13,280
- Don't go that far, Mile.
- No.

1889
01:35:13,360 --> 01:35:16,840
I don't resort to violence
unless it's necessary.

1890
01:35:16,920 --> 01:35:18,720
We lost, and I accept that.

1891
01:35:18,800 --> 01:35:22,120
Because I'm not a professional model,
you know?

1892
01:35:22,200 --> 01:35:24,640
I don't have that much experience.

1893
01:35:24,720 --> 01:35:27,800
Mile will have to fight harder now.
He needs to push himself.

1894
01:35:27,880 --> 01:35:30,960
Normally, rookies make things worse,
but that one is a troublemaker.

1895
01:35:31,040 --> 01:35:33,560
As for Pan, I feel bad for PP.

1896
01:35:33,640 --> 01:35:35,640
He had such sad eyes, Pan.

1897
01:35:35,720 --> 01:35:38,000
He looked so isolated.

1898
01:35:38,080 --> 01:35:42,200
Coming back might not improve
your team's morale.

1899
01:35:42,280 --> 01:35:45,440
So, I decided to send him home.

1900
01:35:45,520 --> 01:35:46,520
I'm not surprised.

1901
01:35:47,440 --> 01:35:49,840
I knew you would make this decision.

1902
01:35:49,920 --> 01:35:51,920
He never intended to give him a chance.

1903
01:35:52,000 --> 01:35:55,040
He wanted to eliminate them.
He was going to anyway.

1904
01:35:55,120 --> 01:35:59,040
Also, the rule is new.
I just wanted to test it out.

1905
01:35:59,120 --> 01:36:02,080
We have someone on a power trip here.

1906
01:36:02,160 --> 01:36:05,520
Having power is quite fun.

1907
01:36:05,600 --> 01:36:08,360
You're getting arrogant. That's arrogance.

1908
01:36:08,440 --> 01:36:11,640
If you don't respect me,
at least respect Panda.

1909
01:36:11,720 --> 01:36:12,920
I'm not being arrogant.

1910
01:36:13,000 --> 01:36:15,760
I'm just savoring my success.

1911
01:36:15,840 --> 01:36:19,320
Power is sweet,
but it will fade away soon.

1912
01:36:19,400 --> 01:36:21,160
Let's go. Leave them here.

1913
01:36:21,240 --> 01:36:22,840
Let's go.

1914
01:36:22,920 --> 01:36:24,280
Let's go.

1915
01:36:24,360 --> 01:36:28,440
Hurry. Things are heating up here.
They even have stones.

1916
01:36:28,520 --> 01:36:32,160
It's weird.
Off didn't seem like himself today.

1917
01:36:32,240 --> 01:36:34,080
It felt more like an act.

1918
01:36:34,160 --> 01:36:36,080
Just swear. Let it out.

1919
01:36:36,160 --> 01:36:37,600
Fuck this!

1920
01:36:37,680 --> 01:36:40,680
At first, I heard "bastard."
Leo, no. You can't say that.

1921
01:36:41,800 --> 01:36:43,720
Oh, that was Korean.

1922
01:36:43,800 --> 01:36:47,720
- Playing a good guy. Like a politician.
- Try to make us believe you're a good guy.

1923
01:36:49,480 --> 01:36:51,160
It's just how my face looks.

1924
01:36:51,920 --> 01:36:52,800
Help me!

1925
01:36:52,880 --> 01:36:53,920
I jumped up.

1926
01:36:54,640 --> 01:36:56,080
Caught it.

1927
01:36:56,160 --> 01:36:57,480
I'm screwed.

1928
01:36:58,040 --> 01:36:59,840
I'm so screwed.

1929
01:37:01,040 --> 01:37:04,080
- Sunscreen…
- The tagline… Everyone is shocked.

1930
01:37:07,120 --> 01:37:10,320
Subtitle translation by: Sarunpon T.
